(324, 1, '<p style="text-align: center;">This is the new Gionee Elife E6,which is designed by the Chinese company Gionee and have made a mark in the world market with OGS that is the One Glass Solution display for the smartphone.This smartphone is built in the Gionee factory from the motherboard till the final hands on experience.Here is a video by IGyaan showing the making and the unboxing of the new Gionee Elife E6.Before going through the video check out the specifications below :</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">GENERAL</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2G Network 850/900/1800/1900 MHz\r\n3G Network 900/2100 MHz\r\nDISPLAY\r\nType 12.7cm (5 “) IPS FHD 1920*1080 OGS, Support 16.7M colors, Gorilla Glass class3\r\nDIMENSION\r\nSIZE 142.5*69.4*7.9mm\r\nDATA\r\n3G/HSPA Yes\r\nGPRS Yes, class 12\r\nEDGE Yes, class 12\r\nWLAN Wifi-802.11 b/g/n, Wi-Fi hotspot\r\nBluetooth v4.0, with A2DP\r\nWireless Input device Yes\r\nOthers WLAN Direct, USB Internet (Sharing Windows PC internet via USB cable), ,Gionee Xender, wireless input device(Keyboard &amp; Mouse)\r\nCAMERA\r\nPrimary 13.0 Mega AF, Auto focus, LED flash\r\nSecondary 5 Mega Pixels, FHD for images.\r\nFeature Face beauty, Panorama(Horizontal &amp; Vertical), Eraser, Face detection, Geo-tagging, Touch focus, 99 snaps in one click, MAV, Gesture Shot, Smile Shot\r\nVideo FHD video recording (Rear Camera)\r\nFEATURES\r\nOS Android OS, v4.2 Jelly bean\r\nCPU Quad core 1.5 GHz Cortex A7\r\nROM 32 GB\r\nGPU PowerVR Series5XT\r\nRAM 2 GB\r\nTF Card NA\r\nBrowser WAP 2.0/xHTML, HTML\r\nAudio DTS 3D Surround Sound\r\nRadio FM Radio\r\nMulti-Media MP3, MP4, H.264/H.263, 3GP, AVI\r\nGPS Yes, with A-GPS Support\r\nSIM Card Single SIM\r\nCompass Digital Compass\r\nSensor Proximity sensor, G-sensor, E-Compass, Gyroscope Sensor, Light Sensor\r\nOthers Smart Gesture, Face Unlock, OTA, Game Zone\r\nBattery 2000mAH\r\nColor White, Black</p>', 'Gionee Elife E6', 'http://codeprogs.wordpress.com/?p=324'),
(363, 1, 'LG G FLEX the worlds first self healing phone and a curved OLED phone.Powered by android Jellybean.Its back has been made by a self healing material which has noot been disclosed by LG. OLED screens produce the best picture quality till date with a very high contrast ratio. The only downside of OLED is that it is very costly to produce. So automatically the cost of any device rises if it has an OLED screen. The estimated price in India according to present price in Korea is 59,000Rs.But adding all custom duties may bring it to more than 70,000Rs which can be very costly for nomal smartphone users.But the smartphone is a revolutionary phone but its self healing technology should be implemented in the future smartphones.\r\n\r\n<strong>Box Contents</strong>\r\n\r\n<img alt="lg-gflex-unboxing_17" src="http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/lg-gflex-unboxing_17.jpg" width="573" height="382" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>LG G Flex  phone which bends!</li>\r\n	<li>AC Wall adapter</li>\r\n	<li>microUSB cable</li>\r\n	<li>SIM ejector pin</li>\r\n	<li>Quadbeat 2 earphones</li>\r\n	<li>Manuals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn terms of the hardware , the G Flex is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 800 processor clocked at 2.26 GHz along with a Adreno 330 GPU with 2GB of RAM. This insanely interesting device features a 6-inch curved P-OLED display and 32GB of on-board storage. The keys are on the back like on the LG G2 and there is a 13MP camera as well along with an LED flash. The phone does feel a lot different in the hand compared to other smartphones out there. The only other smartphone in the market with a curved display is the Samsung Galaxy Round which has a curvature from left to right of the phone and the screen is not flexible.The LG G Flex on the other hand has a curvature from top to bottom or across the length of the device which feels very different.The G Flex is currently on sale only in South Korea and is expected to be available in the US market soon. It 