(374, 1, 'A new phone joins the canvas series of Micromax called as Juice A77.Power all your entertainment with the big and juicy 3000 mAh battery! Discover the delicious Android Jelly Bean OS come to life with the 1.3 GHz Dual core processor. Capture crisp images with its 5 MP camera and view them all on a 12.7 cm (5) screen.Keep all your entertainment going for longer with the ultra long-lasting battery of Canvas Juice!\r\n\r\nAs seen by Micromax till now the battery life had been a problem for some devices.But this time there is a relief for the users.This juice includes a 3000mAh batter,4GB ROM,1GB RAM.Currently listed online in Micromax official website and for now avaiable in Snapdeal the Juice a77 is priced at 8,070 at Snapdeal.com . Some users have commented that the battery has been increased tremendously.\r\n\r\nAlso being a dual SIM phone , with 5.0 inch smartphone adds this phone to the top lists of the Micromax smartphones.It runs Android Jelly Bean 4.2.2 on a dual core MT6572 at 1.3GHz.Primary camera is a 5MP (2592х1944 pixels, autofocus, LED flash),but the secondary camera is VGA one.\r\n\r\nStill the Official price is not on the website but here is screenshot that proves it to be in the range of 8000-10,000.\r\n\r\nHere is a split up of ROM and RAM for the phone.\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="40%">RAM</td>\r\n<td width="1%">:</td>\r\n<td>1 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ROM</td>\r\n<td>:</td>\r\n<td>4 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Internal Memory</td>\r\n<td>:</td>\r\n<td>672 MB (for mass storage), 1.27GB (for apps installation)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Expandable Memory</td>\r\n<td>:</td>\r\n<td>32 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sensors</td>\r\n<td>:</td>\r\n<td>G-Sensor, Promixity Sensor, Light Sensor</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nMT6572 Processor check :\r\n<h3>Features</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>•    <strong>Dual-Core 1.2 GHz CPU</strong>\r\n-    Providing high-end performance with better power efficiency</div>\r\n<div>•    <strong>High-Performance Multimedia Subsystem</strong>\r\n-    Up to 720P 30fps Video Playback and Record\r\n-    5MP Main Camera / 1.3MP sub-Camera\r\n-    qHD (960x540) Display Controller\r\n-    MiraVision™ Display Picture Quality Enhancement</div>\r\n<div>•    <strong>Cost-Optimized System Design for eBOM-Savings</strong>\r\n-    4-Layer PCB Support\r\n-    32K RTC Removal, RF SAW-less\r\n-    GPS co-clock &amp; Integrate external component for Wi-Fi/BT/GPS\r\n-    Wi-Fi/BT/GPS Single Antenna Support (Integrated Connectivity)</div>\r\n</div>\r\nAccording to MediaTek the processor is capable of a video playback of 720p with 30fps.But still the gaming performance and benchmarks are yet to seen.The GPU is not yet disclosed.Its one of the powerful and long lasting device for Micromax!!!', 'Micromax Canvas Juice A77 Review', 'http://freelearn.pixub.com/?p=374'),
(386, 1, 'After the powerful Karbonn Titanium S5 its successor is now available as Titanium S5+.The name gives an idea of some added features to the Titanium S5.Talking about the specs the display is a same size of 5inches i.e. 12.7cms but the S5 has a IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen but S5+ has a qHD Oncell IPS Screen.Dual SIM capable.In terms of software S5 runs on Android 4.1 JB but S5+ runs latest Android 4.2.Both phones has an expandable storage upto 32gb.With S5 Plus User can touch and Swipe gestures along with Voice search and Dialing.But the disappointing thing is battery which is just a 1800mAh in S5+ which is less when compared to S5 having 2000mAh.Here is sneak peak of the specs :\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div>Size</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><label>Weight</label><label>104.5 grams without Battery</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Dimension(mm)</label><label>138*70.5*7.9mm</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Standby time</label><label>up to 4 days</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Talk time</label><label>up to 4 Hrs</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Battery type</label><label>1800mAh</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>SAR Value</label><label>0.326 W/Kg</label></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div>Display</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><label>Screen Type</label><label>OnCell IPS</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Screen Size</label><label>12.7 cm</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Resolution</label><label>540*960 pixels</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Camera</label><label>8 MP Auto Focus</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Vibrator mode</label><label>Yes</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Bluetooth</label><label>Yes</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>Back light of keypad</label><label>Yes</label></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div>Radio Band</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><label>GSM 900, 1800</label><label>900/1800MHz</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>GSM 1900</label><label>Yes</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>EDGE</label><label>Yes</label></li>\r\n	<li><label>GPRS</label><label>Yes</label></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div></li>\r\