(408, 1, 'Now Lets talk about the specifications this phone will come with. The information is also sourced from MMXNewscaster which is well known for leaking MMX official leaks which also holds true most of the time.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/micromax-A350-handset.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-777" alt="micromax-A350-handset" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/micromax-A350-handset.jpg" width="500" height="350" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis is not an official image\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Micromax Canvas 5 Confirmed Specifications</h2>\r\nFirst of all finally you will get a device with more than 3000mAh battery. After <a title="Micromax Canvas Juice With Good Battery Backup" href="http://micromaxcanvas.co.in/canvas-juice-a77-images-3000mah-battery-specs-price-details/" target="_blank">Canvas Juice</a> we’ll see another smartphone with good battery backup.\r\n\r\nA buzz is also there that a new customized UI will be seen in MMX Canvas 5 which is also good.\r\n\r\nSpecs:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>MT6592 Octa Core Processor .</li>\r\n	<li>2GB RAM.</li>\r\n	<li>Customized UI.</li>\r\n	<li>Full HD Display 1080p.</li>\r\n	<li>5 inch screen.</li>\r\n	<li>Internal Storage 16GB.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNow beside these other things are still unknown. What about the Android OS version? Will it be 4.2  again or 4.3?\r\n\r\nSome common things will be there no doubt on that like WiFi, GPS, 3G. Keep checking our blog for more updates.', 'Micromax Canvas 5 Specs Revealed OctaCore Full HD 2GB RAM', 'http://freelearn.pixub.com/?p=408'),
(411, 1, '<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/titaniumx_banner1.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-596" alt="titaniumx_banner1" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/titaniumx_banner1.png" width="562" height="386" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKarbonn has launched the <a href="http://www.fonearena.com/karbonn-titanium-x_4169.html">Titanium X</a>, the company’s latest flagship phone in the Titanium series. It packs a  5.0-inch (1920 x 1080 pixels) IPS display based on One glass solution, powered by 1.5 GHz quad-core processor and runs on Android 4.2 (Jelly Bean). It has a 13-megapixel auto focus rear camera with Dual LED Flash and a 5-megapixel front-facing camera. It has a unibody design, packs 1GB of RAM, 16GB of internal storage and also has expandable memory card slot.\r\n\r\nIt has range of features including Intelligent answer mode, Direct Call, Flip to Mute, Shake to Answer and more.\r\n\r\nHere is quick look of the exact specs as on the official website:\r\n<h2>Karbonn Titanium X detailed specifications</h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>General</strong></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Release date</td>\r\n<td>December 2013</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Form factor</td>\r\n<td>Bar</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Dimensions (mm)</td>\r\n<td>143.90 x 70.50 x 9.90</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Weight (g)</td>\r\n<td>143.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Battery capacity (mAh)</td>\r\n<td>2300</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Removable battery</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Colours</td>\r\n<td>Black, White</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>SAR value</td>\r\n<td>NA</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Display</strong></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Screen size (inches)</td>\r\n<td>5.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Touchscreen</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Touchscreen type</td>\r\n<td>Ca