(470, 1, 'Here is the new Oppo N1 with CyanogenMod launching on 24th of December this year according to the <a href="https://twitter.com/oppo/status/413929425835552768">twitter </a>post by Oppo.The Oppo N1 is the world''s first Google CTS-Certified <a dir="ltr" href="https://twitter.com/CyanogenMod">@CyanogenMod</a> phone!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/1532054_351452768328433_260448811_n.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-544" alt="1532054_351452768328433_260448811_n" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/1532054_351452768328433_260448811_n.png" width="403" height="403" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo buy this though not available in India right now the U.S. store link : <a href="http://oppostyle.com/n1/44-n1-white.html">http://oppostyle.com/n1/44-n1-white.html</a>\r\n\r\nThe Oppo N1 is available on the oppostyle.com at a price of 649$(40228.26Rs)(32gb) and 16gb variant for a price tag of 599$(37129.01Rs) which is a quite high for Indian market and adds into the list of high-end devices.\r\n\r\nOppo N1 is the world''s first phone with rotating camera and also with an Official CyanogenMod Support and now its also CTS-Certified by Google so no need of sideloading the Google apps and the Google Services can now be accessed legitimately.\r\n\r\nThe full specification as listed on the Official Oppo website :\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Processor</td>\r\n<td>Qualcomm Snapdragon 600 Quad-Core 1.7GHz</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Screen</td>\r\n<td>5.9 inch\r\n1080x1920 FULL HD\r\n377 PPI\r\nMulti-touch, capacitive screen, Gorilla Glass 3</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Memory</td>\r\n<td>16GB or 32GB ROM, 2GB RAM DDR3</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Connectivity</td>\r\n<td>UMTS/HSDPA/HSUPA/HSPA+/HSPA+42 (WCDMA 850/900/1700/1900/2100MHz\r\nGSM/EDGE (850/900/1800/1900MHz)\r\n802.11a/b/g/n Wi-Fi (802.11n 2.4GHz and 5GHz)\r\nWi-Fi Direct\r\nBluetooth\r\nNFC</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Features</td>\r\n<td>Android 4.2 (Jelly Bean)\r\nGPS\r\nWi-Fi Display\r\nDLNA\r\nGyroscope\r\nDigital compass\r\nMicrophone\r\nLight Sensor\r\nIR Proximity Sensor\r\nMagnetic Sensor\r\nGravity Sensor</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Battery</td>\r\n<td>Built-in 3610 mAh</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Multimedia</td>\r\n<td>Audio: WAV, AMR, AWB, OGG, WMA, APE, FLAC, MIDI, IMY etc.\r\nVideo: MP4, 3GP, WMV, ASF, AVI, MKV, FLV, MOV, F4V etc.\r\nGraphic: PNG, JPG, BMP, WBMP, GIF etc.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Included Accessories</td>\r\n<td>Device OPPO N1\r\nO-Click Bluetooth Remote Control\r\nIn-ear type earphones\r\nMicro USB cable\r\nCharger\r\nSIM ejector tool</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Camera</td>\r\n<td>13 Megapixel sensor\r\n206 degrees rotating\r\nDual-mode LED\r\nAperture f/2.0</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div></div>', 'Oppo N1 Review', 'http://freelearn.pixub.com/?p=470'),
(476, 1, '<p style="text-align: center;">Xolo LT900 is listed Online on the giant shopping portal <a href="http://www.flipkart.com/xolo-lt900/p/itmdrmh5ahecgg5z?pid=MOBDRMH4SBYNBF2U&amp;affid=gogiincgma">Flipkart</a>,but yet no price is disclosed only a "coming soon" can be seen on the website.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/fimg2.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-555" alt="fimg2" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/fimg2.png" width="649" height="306" /></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The specs are quite interesting and proves to be a high end phone.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;">KEY FEATURES OF XOLO LT900</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<li>1.5 GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon S4 Dual-core Processor</li>\r\n	<li>1 GB RAM and 8 GB Internal Memory and Expandable up to 32 GB</li>\r\n	<li>Corning Glass and Synaptic Touch Controller</li>\r\n	<li>10.92 cm (4.3-inch) HD IPS One Glass Solution Display</li>\r\n	<li>1810 mAh Lithium-ion Battery</li>\r\n	<li>TDD-LTE Band 40: 2300 MHz; 4G Supported</li>\r\n	<li>8 MP Rear Camera with BSI Sensor and 1 MP Front Camera</li>\r\n	<li>Android v4.2 (Jelly Bean) OS</li>\r\n	<li>TDD-LTE: Upto 68 Mbps Download Speed</li>\r\n	<li>384 GHz Adreno 225 GPU</li>\r\n	<li>Airtel Mobile TV and Big Flix and Kepplr Cloud space</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">It accompanies a corning gorilla glass with the new OGS(one glass solution) with an IPS display of 1280 X 720 pixels and with a 5 finger multitouch support.It also comes with an 8 MP primary camera with full HD video recording at 30fps.Internal memory is 8 GB and the RAM of 1GB packed into the phone.Runs on android 4.2.2 Jellybean with the sensors including Gyroscope, Magnetometer, Accelerometer, Ambient Light Sensor, Proximity Sensor.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">A quick look of the full technical specifications :</p>\r\n\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">GENERAL FEATURES</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Brand</td>\r\n<td>XOLO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Model ID</td>\r\n<td>LT900</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Form</td>\r\n<td>Bar</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>SIM Type</td>\r\n<td>Single SIM, GSM</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Touch Screen</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Call Features</td>\r\n<td>Loudspeaker</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Handset Color</td>\r\n<td>Black</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">PLATFORM</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Operating Freq</td>\r\n<td>GSM - 850, 900, 1800, 1900; UMTS - 2100; 4G: TDD-LTE Band 40 - 2300 MHz</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>OS</td>\r\n<td>Android v4.2 (Jelly Bean)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Processor</td>\r\n<td>1.5 GHz Qualcomm MSM8960 Snapdragon S4, Dual Core</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Graphics</td>\r\n<td>Adreno 225, 384 MHz</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">DISPLAY</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Size</td>\r\n<td>4.3 Inches</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Resolution</td>\r\n<td>HD, 1280 x 720 Pixels</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Color</td>\r\n<td>16 M</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Other Display Features</td>\r\n<td>Synaptic Touch Controller, One Glass Solution (OGS), Corning Glass, 5 Fingers Supported, IPS Display</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">CAMERA</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Primary Camera</td>\r\n<td>Yes, 8 Megapixel</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Secondary Camera</td>\r\n<td>Yes, 1 Megapixel</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Video Recording</td>\r\n<td>Yes, 1920 x 1080</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>HD Recording</td>\r\n<td>HD, Full HD</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Other Camera Features</td>\r\n<td>Primary Camera: BSI Sensor, Dual Flash Support, Auto Focus, Image Stabilization, Scene Detection and Tuning, HDR, Low Light Enhancement, Face Recognition (For Focussing as well as in Gallery), Vertical and Horizontal Panorama Capture, Geo-taggingSecondary Camera: 720p Video Recording</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">DIMENSIONS</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Size</td>\r\n<td>66x128.7x9.8 mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">BATTERY</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Type</td>\r\n<td>1810 mAh</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Talk Time</td>\r\n<td>15 hrs (2G), 14 hrs (3G)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Standby Time</td>\r\n<td>362 hrs (2G), 301 hrs (3G)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">MEMORY AND STORAGE</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Internal</td>\r\n<td>8 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Expandable Memory</td>\r\n<td>microSD, upto 32 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Memory</td>\r\n<td>1 GB RAM</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">INTERNET &amp; CONNECTIVITY</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Internet Features</td>\r\n<td>Email</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Preinstalled Browser</td>\r\n<td>Android</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3G</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Wifi</td>\r\n<td>Yes, 802.11 b/g/n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>USB Connectivity</td>\r\n<td>Yes, micro USB, v2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Navigation Technology</td>\r\n<td>A-GPS, with Google Maps</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Bluetooth</td>\r\n<td>Yes, v4</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Audio Jack</td>\r\n<td>3.5 mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">MULTIMEDIA</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Music Player</td>\r\n<td>Yes, Supports MP3, MIDI, WAV</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Video Player</td>\r\n<td>Yes, Supports MPEG4, DivX, MPG, H.264, H.263, MP4, Full HD</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sound Enhancement</td>\r\n<td>Noise and Echo Cancellation Support, Dual Mic</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=" aligncenter" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th colspan="2">OTHER FEATURES</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Call Memory</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>SMS Memory</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Phone Book Memory</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sensors</td>\r\n<td>Gyroscope, Magnetometer, Accelerometer, Ambient Light Sensor, Proximity Sensor</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Additional Features</td>\r\n<td>Android Video Player, Video Chat, Airtel Mobile TV</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Important Apps</td>\r\n<td>Skype, BigFlix, Kepplr Cloud Space</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Key features are 4G, 3G, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth and GPS with A-GPS. This 4G enabled handset is <a href="http://www.flipkart.com/xolo-lt900/p/itmdrmh5ahecgg5z?pid=MOBDRMH4SBYNBF2U&amp;affid=gogiincgma" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">priced at Rs. 16,999</a>. The price seems good specially if you are looking for a smartphone with 4G. The HTC ONE XL that also supports 4G is available for approx Rs. 20,000.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'XOLO LT900 First Xolo 4G LTE available for Rs 16999', 'http://freelearn.pixub.com/?p=476'),
