(804, 1, '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karbonn-a12-plus.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-806" alt="karbonn-a12-plus" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karbonn-a12-plus.jpg" width="467" height="400" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Karbonn''s budget smartphone A12+ is a dual core smartphone running Android 4.2.2 on a 512MB RAM.The internal memory is 1.3GB.The primary camera turns up to be 5MP and a front VGA camera of 0.3MP which is quite impressive specs on a smartphone that comes at a price tag of 4899Rs.The smartphone uses a Mali 400 MP GPU which makes graphics more intutive and smooth.Color saturation is not so evident on this smartphone but can be adjusted as it comes under 5k.</p>\r\n<strong>Karbonn A12+ Specifications</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.0-inch (480 x 800 pixels) capacitive touch screen display</li>\r\n	<li>1.3 GHz dual-core processor</li>\r\n	<li>Dual SIM (GSM + GSM) with Dual Standby</li>\r\n	<li>Android 4.2 (Jelly Bean) OS</li>\r\n	<li>5 MP rear camera with LED flash</li>\r\n	<li>0.3MP (VGA) front-facing camera</li>\r\n	<li>3.5mm audio jack, FM Radio</li>\r\n	<li>3G, Bluetooth, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, micro USB</li>\r\n	<li>512 MB RAM, 4GB of internal memory (1.24 GB user memory), 32GB expandable memory with microSD</li>\r\n	<li>1400 mAh battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGaming on this phone is pretty impressive and is with no lag but a slightly disappointing thing is the color saturation.The black color is dull black and not perfect black and so as white colors.The smartphone tends to favour green color which looks bright and also other colors are nominal.IPS display give wide viewing angle and there is very small fading when you tilt the device.Only battery is of 1400mAh which needs to be tested for standby and talktime hours.But the device perfoms outstanding in the benchmarks.\r\nHere are some popular benchmark scores :\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot-from-2014-01-29-130820.png"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-832" alt="Screenshot from 2014-01-29 13:08:20" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot-from-2014-01-29-130820.png" width="600" height="480" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot-from-2014-01-29-131929.png"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-833" alt="Screenshot from 2014-01-29 13:19:29" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot-from-2014-01-29-131929.png" width="600" height="480" /></a>\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot-from-2014-01-29-130751.png"><img alt="Screenshot from 2014-01-29 13:07:51" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot-from-2014-01-29-130751.png" width="600" height="480" /></a>\r\n\r\nAll Benchmark scores have been taken up from PhoneBunch.com\r\n\r\n[<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=acvm4tcaWYA">SOURCE</a>]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Karbonn A12+ Dual Core Android 4.2 Review', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=804'),
