(917, 1, '<h2>Moto G</h2>\r\nMotorola''s Moto G has gained recognition worldwide with its spectacular specifications and phenomenal price tag.In Indian eBay website the Moto G has been listed on a price tag of Rs 15,995 for the 8GB variant and for the 16 GB variant the price comes around Rs 17,995.And also the Google Play Edition of Moto G on eBay is priced at Rs 21,999.\r\n\r\nYou may also see : <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/android-phone/android-4-4/motorola-moto-g-gets-4-4-2-kitkat-update/">Motorola Moto G gets 4.4.2 Kitkat Update</a>\r\n\r\nLink to the promo page : <a href="http://www.flipkart.com/motorola?utm_campaign=EM-5S31DGFNBGYJ&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=promo&amp;utm_content=click&amp;affid=EM-5S31DGFNBGYJ&amp;cmpid=email_promo_EM-5S31DGFNBGYJ">Click here</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/motog_flipkart.png"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-919" alt="motog_flipkart" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/motog_flipkart-1024x625.png" width="600" height="381" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNow Flipkart is also on the move.Flipkart has created a seprate page for the newly released Moto G.Flipkart is going to market it heavily and there are more demands for the phone until it priced under 15-16k.Since the Update for the phone is Guaranteed more people will want to go with Moto G instead of Indian Companies like Micromax,Kabonn who are not releasing the updates for their phones.\r\n\r\nYou may also see : <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/android-phone/android-4-4/mmx-newscaster-confirms-kitkat-update/">MMX NewsCaster Confirms Kitkat Update</a>\r\n\r\nWe have already gone through the specs of this phone but once again we''ll go through and check out them :\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/moto-g-specs.png"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-921" alt="moto g specs" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/moto-g-specs-1024x360.png" width="600" height="219" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/VunSqD1MOjE" height="315" width="580" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="5"></iframe>\r\n\r\nAnyhow the prices are not officially announced in India but we expect them to be in the range.\r\n<h3>Highlights</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>- 1.2 GHz Quad-Core Qualcomm Snapdragon 400 Processor</li>\r\n	<li>- 1 GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>- 4.5 Inch HD Touchscreen Display</li>\r\n	<li>- 5 MP Rear Camera With LED Flash</li>\r\n	<li>- 1.3 MP Front Camera</li>\r\n	<li>- 3G</li>\r\n	<li>- WiFi</li>\r\n	<li>- Bluetooth v4.0</li>\r\n	<li>- 2070 MAh Battery.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Processor and Memory</h2>\r\nThe good: it’s a reputable processor under the hood. The bad: its performance leaves us yearning for more power. Armed with a quad-core 1.2GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon 400 CPU coupled with 1GB of RAM and the Adreno 305 GPU, it’s effective to handle surface level operations, but it shows its strain and sluggishness with more intensive tasks.\r\n\r\nAvailable in 8GB or 16GB of internal storage, it’s an ample tally that should suffice basic users, but content driven folks can easily fill it up. In that case, cloud storage will increasingly become something they’ll want to invest in.\r\n\r\nBut the performance in turn will consume more battery but the company gives assurance that you will get a battery backup of atmost a day.Lets see how the device performs and we will bring you the detailed review of Moto G when we go hands on.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Moto G on Flipkart : Coming Soon', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=917'),
(978, 5, '<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/images1.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-982" alt="images" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/images1-300x154.jpg" width="300" height="154" /></a>\r\nChinese giant<strong> Oppo</strong> has officially entered the Indian market with the launch of its new phone<strong> Oppo N1</strong>. The company has capped N1 at Rs 39,000. Although it is quite heavily priced for the Indian market, we must not jump to any conclusions before proper assessment of this.\r\n\r\nThe <strong>Oppo N1</strong> will initially be available in 12 cities – <strong>Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai, Bangalore, Hyderabad, Pune, Ahmedabad, Lucknow,Chandigarh, Jaipur and Ludhiana</strong> . The India-specific Oppo site lists three more phones <strong>Oppo Find 5 mini</strong>,<strong> Oppo Neo</strong> and<strong>Oppo R1</strong> is coming soon to India, and we will let you know if and when they do.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Oppo-N1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-980" alt="Oppo N1" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Oppo-N1-300x168.jpg" width="300" height="168" /></a>The USP of the N1 is its rotating<strong> 13MP camera</strong> that can be used as a rear as well as front-facing camera. Oppo says, that the rotation has been tested 100,000 times and this means you can swivel it 40 times a day for 7 years, before it decides to conk off.\r\nBesides, it is also the first phone to officially support <strong>CyanogenMod</strong>, the most popular aftermarket Android ROM.\r\nThe smartphone also runs Oppo’s Color OS, based on<strong> Android 4.2 Jelly Bean</strong>. Sporting a large 5.9-inch 1080p IPS display,it comes powered by a quad-core Snapdragon 600 SoC clocked at 1.7GHz coupled with 2GB of RAM. It offers 16GB and 32GB onboard storage options but there is no room for external memory. The N1 packs in a 3610mAh battery, so at least usage time should be close to if not more than a day. However, we can confirm this only when the device reaches our test labs for a review.\r\nThe connectivity options include 3G, Wi-Fi and Bluetooth. The O Click – a Bluetooth accessory – can be attached in a keyring and used to take pictures remotely or sound an alarm if you can’t find the phone .\r\nFor detailed specifications go to <a href="http://en.oppo.com/products/n1/specs/">http://en.oppo.com/products/n1/specs/ </a>\r\n<p id="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/spin/oppo-n1"><object id="vdo_http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/spin/oppo-n1" style="" width="400" height="450" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="src" value="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/spin/oppo-n1.swf" /><param name="quality" value="high" /><param name="wmode" value="opaque" /><embed id="vdo_http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/spin/oppo-n1" style="" width="400" height="450" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/spin/oppo-n1.swf" quality="high" wmode="opaque" /></object></p>\r\n<b>Double click to spin the image and drag to rotate.</b>', 'Oppo N1 officially arrives in India for a price of Rs. 39,999', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=978'),
