(1023, 1, 'Xolo has launched a new flagship phone the Xolo Q1100.It is definitely a successor for all the models of smartphone Xolo has released.The smartphone is released keeping in mind the release of Moto G and is made to compete with Moto G.The smartphone has similar specs when compared to Moto G but differs in the processor and the display size.The XOLO sports a 5-inch HD display but the Moto G packs a 4.5-inch display.Both the rivals have a 720X1280 pixel display but the Xolo has 294ppi as compared to Moto G''s 326ppi due to increased screen size.But both have a close neighbour the Micromax A250 which has a 441ppi with a MediaTek''s Turbo chipset which is avaiable at a price of Rs16999.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1035" alt="1" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/1.png" width="479" height="946" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe Xolo Q1100 runs Android 4.3 out-of-the-box, the highlight of the device, which makes it the latest Android version in Xolo''s smartphone line-up.\r\n\r\nThe Xolo Q1100 smartphone offers dual-SIM (GSM-GSM) support.It features a 5-inch HD IPS display with a 720x1280 pixel resolution, translating to a pixel density of 294ppi, and boasts One Glass Solution (OGS) which we have talked about earlier. A quad-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 400 (MSM 8228) processor powers the device, clocked at 1.4GHz with an Adreno 305 GPU and 1GB of RAM.\r\n\r\nThe Xolo Q1100 sports an 8-megapixel rear camera with LED flash and BSI 2 sensor, while there is a 2-megapixel front-facing camera. The Xolo Q1100 handset comes with 8GB of in-built storage, and can be expanded up to 32GB via microSD card.\r\n\r\nThe Xolo Q1100 supports Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, GPS, AGPS, EDGE, GPRS and 3G connectivity options. It is backed by a 2000mAh battery, which according to the <a href="http://www.xolo.in/q1100" target="_blank">official site</a> can deliver up to 24 hours of talktime and 600 hours of standby time on 2G network. The Xolo Q1100 is available in Black colour variant.\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/xolo_Q1100_top_banner_02_update.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-1024" alt="xolo_Q1100_top_banner_02_update" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/xolo_Q1100_top_banner_02_update-1024x365.jpg" width="600" height="222" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHowever, its still not been listed on any e-commerce websites but hope to become available on Flipkart soon.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Xolo Q1100 launched at Rs.14999', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1023'),
(1052, 1, 'Google''s new Project Tango has been started and they have built a customized smartphone which is a prototype device for developers to start app development for the customized software.The prototype device runs on Android with customized hardware.\r\n\r\nThe prototype device has a 5'''' screen that tracks the full 3D motion of the smartphone in real time while is also creating the map of the environment.\r\n<blockquote>The goal of Project Tango is to give mobile devices a human-scale understanding of space and motion.\r\n\r\n-  Johnny Lee and the ATAP-Project Tango Team</blockquote>\r\nThe new customized Android running on the device includes development APIs to provide position, orientation, and depth data to standard Android applications written in Java, C/C++, as well as the Unity Game Engine.The device hardware is much more different.These sensors allow the phone to make over a quarter million 3D measurements every second, updating its position and orientation in real-time, combining that data into a single 3D model of the space around you.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/pjt1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1055" alt="pjt1" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/pjt1.png" width="980" height="695" /></a>\r\nThis project has many application from turning your house into a game arena and also the visually-impaired could navigate unassisted in unfamiliar indoor places.You could search for a product and see where the exact shelf is located in a super-store.\r\n\r\nFirst look of the prototype device is here :\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/page_project-tango.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1057" alt="page_project-tango" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/page_project-tango.jpg" width="595" height="531" /></a>\r\n\r\nIf you are a developer and want to try build some good unique and interesting apps for this project you can head to the link : <a href="http://www.google.com/atap/projecttango/">http://www.google.com/atap/projecttango/</a>\r\n\r\nHere is a look of the new Project Tango by Google:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/Qe10ExwzCqk" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Project Tango - 3D Vision to Smartphones by Google', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1052'),
(1062, 2, 'Just 2 days after Facebook bought Whatsapp, the service of the app is now being questioned everywhere, by everyone. This popular app Whatsapp is down from 12:08 am on 23rd February, 2014. The messages are not being sent or received. Also the last seen updation and the login features are not working.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en">sorry we currently experiencing server issues. we hope to be back up and recovered shortly.\r\n\r\n— WhatsApp Status (@wa_status) <a href="https://twitter.com/wa_status/statuses/437319926605680640">February 22, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img alt="Whatsapp goes down" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/1957376_699205050130858_197592354_n-168x300.jpg" />\r\nOn 20th February, Thursday, Facebook agreed to buy this mobile messaging service Whatsapp for $19 billion. As per the terms and conditions of the deal, all the 55 employees of WhatsApp including its founders will be granted restricted stock worth $3 billion that will vest over four years after the deal closes. It''s Facebook''s biggest deal yet and the biggest for an Internet company in more than a decade. And, Zuckerberg reached the deal with Jan Koum in just five days.\r\nFacebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg posted on his Wall, explaining why he bought WhatsApp.\r\nThe text of the letter is given below:\r\n<blockquote>I''m excited to announce that we''ve agreed to acquire WhatsApp and that their entire team will be joining us at Facebook.\r\n\r\nOur mission is to make the world more open and connected. We do this by building services that help people share any type of content with any group of people they want. WhatsApp will help us do this by continuing to develop a service that people around the world love to use every day.\r\n\r\nWhatsApp is a simple, fast and reliable mobile messaging service that is used by over 450 million people on every major mobile platform. More than 1 million people sign up for WhatsApp every day and it is on its way to connecting one billion people. More and more people rely on WhatsApp to communicate with all of their contacts every day.\r\n\r\nWhatsApp will continue to operate independently within Facebook. The product roadmap will remain unchanged and the team is going to stay in Mountain View. Over the next few years, we''re going to work hard to help WhatsApp grow and connect the whole world. We also expect that WhatsApp will add to our efforts forInternet.org, our partnership to make basic internet services affordable for everyone.\r\n\r\nWhatsApp will complement our existing chat and messaging services to provide new tools for our community. Facebook Messenger is widely used for chatting with your Facebook friends, and WhatsApp for communicating with all of your contacts and small groups of people. Since WhatsApp and Messenger serve such different and important uses, we will continue investing in both and making them each great products for everyone.\r\n\r\nWhatsApp had every option in the world, so I''m thrilled that they chose to work with us. I''m looking forward to what Facebook and WhatsApp can do together, and to developing great new mobile services that give people even more options for connecting.\r\n\r\nI''ve also known Jan for a long time, and I know that we both share the vision of making the world more open and connected. I''m particularly happy that Jan has agreed to join the Facebook board and partner with me to shape Facebook''s future as well as WhatsApp''s.\r\n\r\nJan and the WhatsApp team have done some amazing work to connect almost half a billion people. I can''t wait for them to join Facebook and help us connect the rest of the world.</blockquote>\r\nThe service is still (01:30am, 23rd Feb, GMT) down. Let''s hope for some great improvements in Whatsapp!!', 'Whatsapp service goes down', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1062'),
(1082, 1, '<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/7713-bda5009c_680_400.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1085 alignnone" alt="7713-bda5009c_680_400" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/7713-bda5009c_680_400.jpg" width="680" height="400" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMediaTek is widely known for its chipsets for all the mid range phones out there.Most of the phones in India use MT6589 quad core chipsets which is becoming the cheapest quad core option for the Smartphone producers.\r\n\r\nNow its time for the company to announce the first 64-bit Octa Core processor.The process is named as MT6572 and is a 64-bit processor.The company announced it at the MWC 2014 in Barcelona.\r\n\r\nFor MWC Conference Schedule : <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/mwc">Here</a>\r\n\r\nThe SoC is pin compatible with its quad core MT6732 chipset.The chipset supports LTE and is coupled with Mali-T760 GPU and is aimed at the super-mid market.It has eight 64-bit ARM Cortex-A53 cores.\r\n\r\n<strong>Highlights of MediaTek MT6752 Octa-Core SoC</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2 GHz ARM octa-core Cortex-A53 64-bit CPUs</li>\r\n	<li>Mali-T760 GPU with support for the Open GL ES 3.0 and Open CL 1.2 APIs</li>\r\n	<li>1080p, 30fps video playback, H.265 and legacy H.264</li>\r\n	<li>1080p, 30fps H.264 video recording</li>\r\n	<li>Up to 16MP camera image signal processor (ISP)</li>\r\n	<li>MediaTek ClearMotion technology for smooth video playback at 60fps on mobile devices</li>\r\n	<li>MediaTek MiraVision technology for DTV-grade picture quality</li>\r\n	<li>Integrated Multi-mode 4G LTE Modem – Rel. 9, Category 4 FDD and TDD LTE (150 Mb/s downlink, 50 Mb/s uplink)</li>\r\n	<li>3GPP Rel. 8, DC-HSPA+ (42 Mb/s downlink, 11 Mb/s uplink), TD-SCDMA and EDGE are supported for legacy 2G/3G networks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe production and the availability of the chipset for the Smartphone manufacturers to use it in their phones is approximately stated to be ready in Q4 of this year.\r\n\r\nFor MWC 2014 Conference and Keynote Schedules visit <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/mwc">Here</a>.', 'MediaTek announced the first 64-bit Octa Core SoC', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1082');
