(1089, 1, 'Since, we all know that we have a lot of inclination to the free open source and user friendly Android platforms for the smartphones but we had been questioning why Nokia is not in the Android Race as other LG,Samsung are.Since they have seen a whole decline in the market share of windows phones and Nokia is now turning its face towards Android but not the Vanilla/Customized but a foarked version of Android which is customized and made to run FastLane as in Nokia Asha Series.Nokia has also added this Nokia X Series to Asha Series of phones which include FastLane.\r\n\r\nNokia was working on this project since last year and we had been seeing many photo leaks of Normandy on evleaks.com.The X was previously under development known as <b>Normandy</b>, <b>Project N</b>, the <b>Asha on Linux project</b> and <b>MView</b>.Finally Nokia has made a great marketing opportunity of announcing its debut forked Android phones in the MWC 2014.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Nokia-X-Dual-SIM-front.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1090" alt="Nokia-X-Dual-SIM-front" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Nokia-X-Dual-SIM-front.png" width="248" height="450" /></a>\r\n\r\nThere are models of Normany X,X+,XL.X,+ have a screen size of 4" with 233 dpi display.The resolution is 480 X 800.\r\n\r\nThe specs are almost like a mid-range smartphone with Snapdragon S4 chipset which is a dual core processor clocked at 1Ghz Cortex A5.Only difference is that X has a 512MB RAM and X+,XL has 768MB of RAM.Both run a forked version of Android JellyBean 4.1.2.The phone doesn''t include Google Apps but have a set of Nokia apps which perform the same.You have a Nokia Store instead of Google Play but the apps are still limited.\r\n\r\nHighlighted Specs:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Main camera sensor: 3 MP</li>\r\n	<li>Display size: 4''''</li>\r\n	<li>Processor name: Qualcomm Snapdragon™ S4</li>\r\n	<li>Maximum talk time (3G): 10.5h</li>\r\n	<li>Maximum music playback time: 26h</li>\r\n	<li>Photo sharing: Twitter;Facebook;Send as email attachment;Share over Bluetooth</li>\r\n	<li>Social apps: Facebook;Twitter;WeChat;Viber;Skype</li>\r\n	<li>Sensors: Ambient light sensor, Accelerometer, Proximity sensor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe phone supports a 2-point multitouch and is an IPS LCD display.The software update will be over the air(FOTA).\r\n\r\nThe photography features of X,X+,XL:\r\n<ul id="photography">\r\n	<li>Main camera\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Main camera sensor: 3 MP</li>\r\n	<li>Camera resolution: 2048 x 1536 pixels</li>\r\n	<li>Main camera focus type: Fixed focus</li>\r\n	<li>Camera digital zoom: 4 x</li>\r\n	<li>Sensor size: 1/5 inch</li>\r\n	<li>Main camera f-number/aperture: f/2.8</li>\r\n	<li>Camera focal length: 32.4 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Camera minimum focus range: 50 cm</li>\r\n	<li>Camera image formats: JPEG</li>\r\n	<li>Flash type: No Flash</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Main camera features\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Main camera - other features: Auto and manual white balance, Active toolbar, Still image editor, Face recognition, Auto exposure, Center weighted auto exposure</li>\r\n	<li>Digital camera add-ons: Panorama lens</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Image capturing\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Capture modes: Panorama, Video, Still</li>\r\n	<li>Colour tone modes: Sepia, Solarize, Normal, Negative</li>\r\n	<li>White balance modes: Cloudy, Incandescent, Fluorescent, Daylight, Automatic</li>\r\n	<li>Light sensitivity: Automatic, ISO 100, ISO 200, ISO 400</li>\r\n	<li>Photos viewed by: Album, Timeline</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBut the Nokia XL introduces a 5-inch display.And also has a 5MP camera compared to 3.15MP in X,X+.Its proven to be like a successor to X,X+.Like Micromax Canvas XL this is again Nokia here making a huge display with Nokia XL.More things like rooting,custom ROMs,and Gapps are being ported.Just leave your comments below if you want to know more about Nokia''s "Android" Phones.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Nokia Finally turning it down to Android : Nokia Normandy X,X+,XL', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1089'),
(1094, 1, 'After releasing the Nokia X,X+,XL at MWC 2014 by Nokia everybody knew that this would happen.It happened so soon.Yes Nokia X has been rooted and Google Play Apps has been loaded into it.All the credits goes to XDA.The recent news on XDA confirmed the rooting and gapps installation.\r\n\r\nFor Nokia X Owners this is a chance to enjoy Google Apps on their device.And also the CWM and custom ROMs are on the way.This is not new for an Android phone user.But if CWM and Custom ROMs come then Nokia X is not more than a normal Android Dual Core Phone.\r\n\r\nOfficial link for the thread/guide to root and Install Gapps is here : <a href="http://www.xda-developers.com/android/nokia-x-rooted-and-loaded-with-google-apps-play-store-and-google-now-launcher/" target="_blank">Link</a>\r\n\r\nAll thanks to Framaroot again for rooting the new Nokia X using the gandalf exploit.\r\n\r\nThe pic says it all:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/2014-02-28_17.38.15-767x1024.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1096" alt="2014-02-28_17.38.15-767x1024" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/2014-02-28_17.38.15-767x1024.jpg" width="767" height="1024" /></a>\r\n\r\nEven the Google''s New Launcher has been installed on the Nokia replacing the FastLane.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/NRjbR8RmWPs" height="325" width="600" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Nokia X Rooted and Loaded with Google Play Apps', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1094'),
(1099, 1, 'Android Coffee table a concept is now shaped into reality by ideum an app developing and touch table producing company.Before this table was running Windows 7 and 8.And now they have recently announced that an Android version will be in the way later this year.\r\n\r\nYou can check out the table at official site <a href="http://ideum.com/coffee-tables/" target="_blank">here</a>\r\n\r\nThe table comes in a display size of 46" or 32" and can be chosen by you.Even the software if requested is also degraded to windows 7 in windows running coffee table.The table includes a Intel Quad Core i7 chipset which gives the seamless multitasking in windows as well as Android.The display shows a 3M Projected Capacitive Technology.It also has Intel''s WiDi the wireless display to share your content through HDMI devices.The Platform Multitouch Coffee Tables come complete with Ethernet, WiDi capability,\r\nWiFi (Wireless N), and Bluetooth connectivity. They also include USB, DVI, VGA, HDMI, and DP access ports.\r\n\r\nThe Android Coffee Table will run JellyBean 4.1 with x86 Intel''s compatibility of Android.The price is less than 7000$.And this table is made to create an technical ambiance and also gives you wings and saves your time while having a coffee you can look at news,play games,and much more.\r\n\r\nSpecifications of 32" Multitouch Coffee Table:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/specs.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1100" alt="specs" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/specs.png" width="787" height="304" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n46" Specs:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/specs1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1101" alt="specs1" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/specs1.png" width="768" height="317" /></a>\r\n\r\nQuick look of the table in a promo video below:\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/x2RwzFAcKrU" height="445" width="800" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Its not just a coffee table : Its an Android running giant', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1099'),
(1104, 1, '<p>Micromax has added a 3G enabled tablet again to its lineup of Funbook Tabs.This tab is a bit different.It has 7.8" HD display with 1.2 GHz Quad Core chipset with 1GB of RAM.It got listed on HomeShop 18 and is In Stock and Avaiable for Rs11990.Its called as Micromax Funbook Ultra HD P580.</p>\r\n<p>It has rear camera of 5MP and a front camera of 3MP and also has 3G and WiFi connectivity.It packs a 3600mAh battery and is a significance increase in terms of battery for the Micromax devices.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Tablet Features</p>\r\n<table cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Processor</td>\r\n<td>1.2 GHz Quad Core</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Operating System</td>\r\n<td>Android</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>OS Version</td>\r\n<td>4.2.2 Jelly Bean</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sensors</td>\r\n<td>Gravity Sensor, Accelerator Sensor</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Memory</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>RAM</td>\r\n<td>1 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Internal Storage</td>\r\n<td>8 GB ROM</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Expandable Storage</td>\r\n<td>Upto 32 GB using Micro SD</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Although its not yet listed on the Micromax Official Site.If you wanny buy one hurry now!!!</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.homeshop18.com/micromax-funbook-ultra-hd-p580-7-8-inch-19-8-cm-android-calling-tablet-silver/computers-tablets/tablets/product:31653037/cid:16325" target="_blank">Link to HS18</a></p>\r\n', 'Micromax Funbook Ultra HD P580 With 7.8″ HD Display Listed on HS18', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1104'),
(1114, 1, 'Cortana the new Voice Assistance App for Windows Phone is spotted online.Like the Google Now in Android and Siri in iPhone,Microsoft has introduced Cortana for Windows Phone 8.1.The app shows a blue ring in the centre of the screen instead of the much anticipated female animation which was expected.Below it has a search bar with microphone icon next to it and also shows a music icon along with an icon on the top right which is expected to be for the "settings" page.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/cortana_windowsphone_screenshots-580-100.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1115" alt="cortana_windowsphone_screenshots-580-100" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/cortana_windowsphone_screenshots-580-100.jpg" width="580" height="326" /></a><em>PC : The Verge</em>\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/wkgJwGzsn3Y" height="415" width="660" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="1"></iframe>', 'Windows Phone 8.1''s Voice Assistance App - Cortana', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1114'),
(1119, 1, '<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/1901592_676580802405226_541097980_n.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1121 alignnone" alt="1901592_676580802405226_541097980_n" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/1901592_676580802405226_541097980_n.jpg" width="873" height="960" /></a>\n\nFinally, the most anticipated and a low cost octa core smartphone Micromax Canvas Knight A350 is listed in Flipkart as Coming Soon.The smartphone was announced long back last year but was released in Russia and later in India.You can always buy the smartphone from Micromax Store i.e. from the official website.\n\nNow you can also buy from Flipkart.The smartphone is running Android 4.2.2 but the design of the phone is similar to iPhone including the back mat finish.\n\nThe specs round-up is here : <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/micromax/canvas/micromax-canvas-knight-a350-first-octa-core-smartphone/" target="_blank">Click Here</a>\n\nYou can buy the phone here : <a href="http://www.flipkart.com/micromax-canvas-knight-350/p/itmdttbk3bhzgrry?pid=MOBDUYY8CHZZRSGK&amp;srno=t_1&amp;query=micromax+canvas+a350&amp;affid=itechnosp" target="_blank">Flipkart Link</a>\n\n&nbsp;\nImage originally published at <a href="http://images.maxabout.com/misc/infographics/image/micromax-canvas-knight-a350-specifications-and-expected-price">Maxabout</a>\n&nbsp;', 'Micromax Canvas Knight A350 ''Coming Soon'' on Flipkart', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1119'),
(1154, 2, '[caption id="attachment_1159" align="alignright" width="210"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/ISP0042PRK.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1159" alt="Internshala Training Courses" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/ISP0042PRK-210x300.png" width="210" height="300" /></a> ISP0042PRK[/caption]\r\n\r\nAre you a <strong><span style="color: green;">1st year</span></strong> or <strong><span style="color: green;">2nd year</span></strong> student and would rather learn a new technology skill this summer that would help you kickstart your career than spend time on Facebook getting bored?\r\nOr are you a <strong><span style="color: green;">pre-final year student</span></strong> and would rather do a meaningful training where you learn a new technology than a Ctrl+C - Ctrl+V internship?\r\nOr are you thinking of doing something <em><strong><span style="color: green;">constructive this summer</span></strong></em> ?\r\nThen <strong><span style="color: red;">VTC</span></strong> is just for you: "<strong><span style="color: red;">Internshala, Virtual Training Center</span></strong>".\r\n\r\nVTC is offering 8 Internshala certified summer trainings in<strong></strong>\r\n<ul style="color: red;">\r\n	<li>Web Development</li>\r\n	<li>Core Java</li>\r\n	<li>Hacking</li>\r\n	<li>ASP . NET</li>\r\n	<li>Windows 8 App Development</li>\r\n	<li>Python</li>\r\n	<li>Robotics</li>\r\n	<li>VLSI design</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nthat you can sign up for.\r\nVisit this <strong><a href="http://vtc.internshala.com/?utm_source=ISP&amp;utm_medium=ISP0042PRK">website</a></strong> and choose from for an exciting range of ONLINE summer training programs by Internshala in the above mentioned fields.\r\nSign up now using promo code "<strong><span style="color: red;">ISP0042PRK</span></strong>" and avail <span style="color: red;">15% exclusive discount</span> on the training fee.\r\n<blockquote><strong><span style="color: red;">Early-bird discounts are also available if you pay before 21st April, so sign up today.</span></strong></blockquote>\r\nSo, which of the 8 technologies will you learn this summer?', 'Internshala Online Summer Training Courses 2014', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1154'),
(1170, 1, 'Karbonn has teamed up with MediaTek to bring Hexa and Octa Core under 20k and eventually within the mid-range phones.This is the Karbonn Titanium Hexa which is again is priced at 16,990 INR which comes in a mid range smartphone.The best feature of this smartphone is that it comes with Android Kitkat 4.4.2 out of the box and has almost all important sensors like Accelerometer,Proximity and Magnetic Field Sensors.\r\n<h3>Key Specs</h3>\r\n<table width="358" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Model</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">Karbonn Titanium Hexa</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Display</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">5.5 Inch , 1080p Full HD</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Processor</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">1.5 GHz Hexa Core MT6591</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">RAM</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">2 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Internal Storage</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">16 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">OS</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">Android 4.4 KitKat</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Camera</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">13 MP/ 5 MP</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Battery</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">2050 mAh</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Price</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">16,900 INR</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe phone comes with a 5.5 inch LTPS display with 1920 x 1080p full HD resolution. The operating system is latest Android 4.4 KitKat and that does make this phone stand apart from the competition.\r\n\r\nThe Hexa core processor is clocked at 1.5 GHz. Chipset details have not been specified yet. The phone might feature <a href="http://gadgetstouse.com/news/eynos-5422-exynos5460/15814">Exynos 5 Hexa 5260</a> chipset unveiled at MWC, but most likely it will come with MediaTek MT6591 Hexa core which is still unofficial.\r\n\r\nStill other companies like Micromax and Intex has already launched their Octa Core devices but this device overcomes as it has Android Kitakat so as for now no issues of updates.This can be result of Google''s new rules that the upcoming phones should have Kitkat so that it can be approved by their Labs.\r\n<blockquote>Starting February 2014, Google will no longer approve GMS distribution on new Android products that ship older platform releases,” explains the document. “Each platform release will have a ‘GMS approval window’ that typically closes nine months after the next Android platform release is publicly available. (In other words, we all have nine months to get new products on the latest platform after its public release.)</blockquote>\r\nStay tuned for more updates on where and how to buy this phone.We''ll be updating the post soon!!!!\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Karbonn Titanium Hexa with Android Kitkat and Hexa Core', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1170'),
(1176, 1, 'Karbonn is back again with a bang.Its first Octa Core Phone in the Titanium Series is here.Its the Karbonn Titanium Octane Plus.The smartphone has a good sleeky design and as of specifications it comes with a 5 inch Full HD 1920 X 1080 display (441 ppi pixel density)and 2gb of RAM with MediaTek MT6592 1.7 Ghz Octa Core with Android Kitkat 4.4.2 out of the box.It features a 16 MP rear autofocus camera and with an 8 MP front facing camera for better video calling.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/large_pro_detail_1_206.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1179" alt="large_pro_detail_1_206" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/large_pro_detail_1_206.png" width="250" height="515" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/large_pro_detail_3_206.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1180" alt="large_pro_detail_3_206" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/large_pro_detail_3_206.png" width="250" height="515" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/large_pro_detail_2_206.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1181" alt="large_pro_detail_2_206" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/large_pro_detail_2_206.png" width="250" height="515" /></a>\r\n\r\nKarbonn has announced three smart-phones this year.We have already gone through the review of <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/karbonn/karbonn-titanium-hexa-android-kitkat-hexa-core/">Karbonn Titanium Hexa.</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Key Specs</h3>\r\n<table width="358" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Model</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">Karbonn Titanium Octane</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Display</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">5.0 Inch , 1080p Full HD</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Processor</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">1.7 GHz Octa Core MT6592</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">RAM</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">2 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Internal Storage</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">16 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">OS</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">Android 4.4 KitKat</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Camera</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">16 MP/ 8 MP</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Battery</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">2000 mAh</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="168">Price</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="188">17,900 INR</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The smartphones are the flagship phones for Karbonn and are expected to hit the markets in the first week of April.\r\nPost will be updated soon with online sites which are selling the handsets and more!!!</div>', 'Karbonn Titanium Octane Plus - Octa Core and Android Kitkat', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1176'),
(1257, 1, 'Wickedleak has launched Wammy Titan Octa 3 its first octa core smartphone in India for just Rs 14,990.The company is well known for its clone phones of flagship smartphones released by companies like Samsung.This smartphone is a successor of Wammy Titan 3 which is a quad core device.The device has a 5.7 inch-IPS WXGA 800 x 1280 pixel display which also gives a good and wide viewing angles.The smartphone also comes with an optional  AquaProtect hydrophobic coating, for an additional Rs. 1,500. This is the company''s second octa-core offering, after the <a href="http://gadgets.ndtv.com/wickedleak-wammy-passion-x-1330">Wammy Passion X</a>.The screen is protected with OGS Dragon Trail glass.\r\n<h2>Wickedleak Wammy Titan 3 Octa detailed specifications</h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>General</strong></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Release date</td>\r\n<td>March 2014</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Form factor</td>\r\n<td>Touchscreen</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Dimensions (mm)</td>\r\n<td>141.00 x 65.00 x 8.95</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Weight (g)</td>\r\n<td>150.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Battery capacity (mAh)</td>\r\n<td>3200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Removable battery</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Colours</td>\r\n<td>Black, White</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>SAR value</td>\r\n<td>NA</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Display</strong></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Screen size (inches)</td>\r\n<td>5.70</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Touchscreen</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Touchscreen type</td>\r\n<td>Capacitive</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Resolution</td>\r\n<td>800x1280 pixels</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Hardware</strong></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Processor</td>\r\n<td>1.7GHz  octa-core</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Processor make</td>\r\n<td>MediaTek MT6592</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>RAM</