(1267, 16, 'The post aims at comparing the functionality of <strong>getche()</strong>, <strong>getchar()</strong> and <strong>getch()</strong>....\r\n\r\nLet us look at the following 3 code snippets:\r\n\r\n<strong>Snippet 1</strong>:\r\nmain()\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;char ch=getch();\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;cout&lt;&lt;endl&lt;&lt;ch;\r\n}\r\n\r\n<strong>Snippet 2</strong>:\r\nmain()\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;char ch=getche();\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;cout&lt;&lt;endl&lt;&lt;ch;\r\n}\r\n\r\n<strong>Snippet 3</strong>:\r\nmain()\r\n{\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;char ch=getchar();\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;cout&lt;&lt;endl&lt;&lt;ch;\r\n}\r\n\r\nThe output for the 3 snippets are as follows....\r\n\r\n<strong>For the first one</strong>:\r\n\r\na\r\n\r\n<strong>For the second one</strong>:\r\na\r\na\r\n\r\n<strong>For the third one</strong>:\r\na\r\n\r\na\r\n\r\n(for all snippets we assume that the value input is a)\r\n\r\nNotice that in the third snippet there is an extra line between the two a''s.\r\n\r\nNow let''s understand the execution of the programs-\r\n\r\n<strong>For snippet 3:\r\ngetchar(): </strong>\r\n\r\nWhen value a is given, it is stored in the variable "ch" through getchar() which serves the purpose of taking in the input, but at the same time by default it also prints the value  which is given as the input.\r\n\r\nThe further execution of the code is stopped until the ENTER key is pressed.After pressing the ENTER key the next line i.e. cout&lt;&lt;endl&lt;&lt;ch; is executed and hence  we get the output\r\n\r\na\r\n\r\na\r\n\r\n<strong>For snippet 2:\r\ngetche():</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen the input a is  given, getche() serves the purpose of storing and printing (like getchar()) i.e when the input is given  a is stored in ch and printed simualtaneously (by default). After printing ,the remaining code is executed without waiting for any other input(unlike getchar() where we need to press the ENTER key).\r\n\r\nSo the next line i.e. cout&lt;&lt;endl&lt;&lt;ch; is executed and hence we get the second a (NOTICE: the second a is printed without any  additional line  in between as we are not pressing the ENTER key).\r\n\r\n<strong>For snippet 1:\r\ngetch():</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen we give the input as a,the value is stored in ch ,i.e getch() serves the purpose of  reading the value from the user (like getchar() and getche()). But it does not print the input value by default (unlike getche() and getchar()).\r\n\r\nOnce the value is given the further code is executed without waiting for any other input (unlike getchar()).\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<em>Hence, we get the following conclusions:\r\n\r\n<strong>getch(): </strong>Does not print the value by default and the further code  is executed without waiting for any further input.\r\n\r\n<strong>getche():</strong> Prints the value by default and the further code is executed without waiting for any input.\r\n\r\n<strong>getchar():</strong>Prints the value and waits for enter to be pressed so that the further code can be executed.</em>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nHope you liked the blog...!!\r\n...Presented by Ankit Rai and Trushangi Pradhan.\r\n\r\nStay tuned for more blogs...\r\n\r\nAlso see: <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/computer-science/algorithms/bubble-sort-program-c-cplus/">Bubble Sort</a>', 'getchar( )  v/s  getche( )  v/s  getch( )', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1267'),
(1285, 1, 'Hey guys,this post is purely on Android Kernel Development.The post basically is for all the android enthusiasts out there, trying to get their hands on the kernel development.This tutorial gives the step by step instructions for building kernel from the source.\r\n\r\nI am using Ubuntu 13.10.You can use any of the Linux distro available. But the packages required, depends on the Linux distro you are on.\r\n\r\nBefore you start nailing you need some packages to be installed for compiling the kernel.The packages can be installed by the following command.Open the terminal and paste the following code:\r\n\r\n<code>sudo apt-get install -y build-essential kernel-package libncurses5-dev bzip2</code>\r\n\r\nNext step is to download the sources.You can get sources from <a href="htcdev.com">htcdev.com</a>. As I am using HTC Explorer for the demo, you can get the source for your device from the below sites.\r\n<blockquote><code>Websites for Kernel Sources:</code>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.htcdev.com/">http://www.htcdev.com/</a>\r\n<a href="http://opensource.samsung.com/">http://opensource.samsung.com/</a>\r\n<a href="http://developer.sonymobile.com/wportal/devworld/search-downloads/opensource">http://developer.sonymobile.com/wportal/devworld/search-downloads/opensource</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.lg.com/global/support/opensource/opensource.jsp">http://www.lg.com/global/support/opensource/opensource.jsp</a></blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNext step is to download the toolchain from google repo. You can use any other repo also, as the toolchains from Google sometimes needs to be modified in order to get success in compiling kernels. Some of the develpers also said that the toolchain was breaking the wifi module. So for this tutorial the toolchain from <a href="https://github.com/DooMLoRD/android_prebuilt_toolchains">DooMLoRD''s</a> repo is used.\r\n\r\nOpen Terminal and make a directory for our toolchains.\r\n<code>mkdir ~/toolchain</code>\r\nWill create a directory in the home folder.\r\nThen move into the created folder by\r\n<code>cd ~/toolchain</code>\r\nNow from the terminal clone the repo using\r\n<code>git clone https://github.com/DooMLoRD/android_prebuilt_toolchains.git</code>\r\nThis will clone the repository and will download all the toolchain files to your toolchain folder.Now your toolchain folder will contain another folder called as "android_prebuilt_toolchains" and inside that folder you will have three other folders:\r\n<ul>arm-eabi-4.4.3</ul>\r\n<ul>arm-eabi-linaro-4.6.2</ul>\r\n<ul>arm-linux-androideabi-4.7</ul>\r\n<strong>NOTE:If you don''t have git installed then use this command to install git\r\n<code>apt-get install git</code></strong>\r\n\r\nHere the downloaded kernel zip file for our kernel is pico-gb-crc-2.6.38-207b2e1.zip.\r\n\r\nWe unzip the file to get two files:\r\n<ul>pico-gb-crc-2.6.38-207b2e1.tar.gz</ul>\r\n<ul>pico_readme.txt</ul>\r\nThe toolchain specified here in the readme file is the toolchain-eabi-4.4.3.For that purpose we will be using the arm-eabi-4.4.3 downloaded from the DooMLoRD''s repo.\r\n\r\nThe directory I am using here for my pico kernel source : ~/android/kernel/pico-gb\r\nThe path of my toolchain : ~/android/toolchain/android_prebuilt_toolchains/arm-eabi-4.4.3/bin/arm-eabi-\r\n\r\nSome kernel uses different toolchains.But if you download kernel source from htcdev in the zip filef you will get a notepad file containing the make config and the toolchain used.For other vendors like samsung,sony sources you need to lookup for the toolchains in the readme files.\r\n\r\nInstructions:\r\n<strong>(Don''t do any changes in the .bashrc for the toolchain''s path)</strong>\r\n<ol>1.cd to the directory of your kernel source.</ol>\r\n<ol>2.export ARCH=arm</ol>\r\n<ol>3.export CROSS_COMPILE=~/android/toolchain/android_prebuilt_toolchains/arm-eabi-4.4.3/bin/arm-eabi-</ol>\r\n<ol>4.make clean &amp;&amp; make mrproper</ol>\r\n<ol>5.make msm7627a_defconfig</ol>\r\n<ol>6.make menuconfig</ol>\r\n<ol>7.make</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAfter the sucessful build you will get the zImage and the drivers(*.ko) files.\r\n<strong>Files path:</strong>\r\n<strong> arch/arm/boot/zImage</strong>\r\n<strong> drivers/*/*.ko</strong>\r\n\r\nNow use the AnyKernel.zip(<a href="http://www.wuala.com/itechnospot/kernel%20tutorial/k-any-kern.zip/">download link here</a>) file by Koush to flash the zImage and the drivers.Use archive manager or any other zip file manager to open the zip.Get the zImage and copy it into the kernel folder with the archive still open and also the drivers in system/lib/modules folder in the zip file.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do not extract the zip file as the zip file is signed with particular keys which on unzipping will lose its signing and it won''t be installed from your recovery.</strong>\r\n\r\nThen the zip file is ready to flash and once you flash it its your own kernel and you have compiled it.Now go ahead tweaking the kernel for more optimizations.For more kernel tweaking tutorials stay tuned and subscribe to our <a href="http://www.youtube.com/itechnospot" target="_blank">Youtube Channel</a> for more videos.\r\n\r\nThis method can be applicable to any kernel you are building for your smart phone.Hope you liked the tutorial.If you liked it share and like us on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/itechnospot" target="_blank">Facebook Page</a>.Any queries or comments please leave it below.\r\n\r\nCredits:DooMLoRD,Koush and XDA\r\n\r\n<center><em><strong>Like us on Facebook:</strong> </em></center>\r\n<div class="fb-like" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/itechnospot" data-width="100" data-layout="standard" data-action="like" data-show-faces="false" data-share="false"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Android Kernel Building Tutorial', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1285'),
(1308, 1, '<h4><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/WindowsPhone8.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1365" alt="WindowsPhone8" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/WindowsPhone8-1024x433.png" width="580" height="245" /></a></h4>\r\n<h4>Windows Phone 8.1 Update has bought a bunch of new and some existing features in the update.The phone volume and music volume are now independent,the new parallex effect and changing the start screen background and also the <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/windows-phone-8-1s-voice-assistance-app-cortana/">Cortana</a>.Lets check out 3 new things in detail.We have already checked out the new <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/windows-phone-8-1s-voice-assistance-app-cortana/">Personal Assistane Cortana.</a></h4>\r\n<pre><strong>See this : <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/windows-phone-8-1s-voice-assistance-app-cortana/">http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/windows-phone-8-1s-voice-assistance-app-cortana/</a></strong></pre>\r\n<h4><strong>Action Center</strong> : This is the notification center for WP after the toast notifications till WP8.There is way no way back to see the missed out notification in previous versions.The notification center resembles the Android''s notification center but still needs to be improved a lot.There are only 4 quick toggles you get.They are WiFi,Bluetooth,Airplane and Orientation settings.Below the orientation button you get the settings button which takes you to the usual settings panel.The Action Center can be swiped at any time from the top to see the notifications.You can clear the notification all at once or can swipe them individually.As you swipe down the notification center the background slightly gets darkened like seen in Android JellyBean.The status bar is always shown as in the previous versions you need to tap twice for the status bar to display from the top with bounce animations.</h4>\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/IMG-20140420-WA0000.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1338" alt="IMG-20140420-WA0000" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/IMG-20140420-WA0000-180x300.jpg" width="180" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/IMG_20140415_093756.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1310" alt="IMG_20140415_093756" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/IMG_20140415_093756-225x300.jpg" width="225" height="300" /></a>\r\n<h4><strong>Better Volume Control :</strong> Now the ringer volume and the music volume are separate and can be adjusted independently.You can set your ringer and notification value separately and put your music volume on max.And also you can set your headphone volume separately when you plug in your headphones.</h4>\r\n<h4><strong>The Start Screen Background and the "parallex" effect :</strong></h4>\r\n<h4>The background can now be customized and the background of tiles can also be changed.The background of the tiles actually create a parallex effect making the scrolling experience amazing.Many people like to scroll to see this effect again and again.</h4>\r\n<h4>Windows phone update has been rolled out for developers now yet many people say the battery backup is not good.But since it is an early developers update much more changes can come in the consumer update.</h4>\r\n<h3>If you want to update your windows phone to latest 8.1 update you need to do the following steps:</h3>\r\n<h4>Register as developer using the <span style="color: #993366;"><a href="http://appstudio.windowsphone.com/"><span style="color: #993366;">AppStudio</span></a></span> for free.Use same email address which you use in your windows phone to register.Then download <a href="http://www.windowsphone.com/en-us/store/app/preview-for-developers/178ac8a1-6519-4a0b-960c-038393741e96">Preview for Developers</a> app.Open the app agree terms and conditions and sign-in using the same email address.Then agree to enable the app and then click done.</h4>\r\n<h4>Now move to settings of your phone and click on phone update and tap check for updates.It will check for updates and since you are now registered as a developer it will show that a developer update is available.Click download and the download begins.Thats it now after the download finishes,it installs the update and now you have WP8.1 in your device.</h4>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Windows Phone 8.1 Update - 3 New Things', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1308'),
(1344, 1, 'If you are a group admin and annoyed of your group notifications of posts and new members requesting to join the group here is a new feature from Facebook to help you out.\r\n\r\nFacebook adds the Groups You Admin option under the Groups tab.Now its easy to navigate through the groups you admin and makes your work a lot more easier.Now you can create groups from the group you admin tab and you also get the settings icon for each group where you can also edit the group notification settings,group settings,add the group to favourites list and also can leave the group.\r\n\r\nThe Groups You Admin also shows you the notifications with respect to the groups like (10+ unread posts,2 pending actions) and so on.The feature is just yet arrived and is of a greater help to the group admins.Though this is not a feature where other than group admins can enjoy its benefits.But since majority people are group admin on Facebook the feature is great.\r\n\r\n<center><br /><div style="width: 450px; border-radius: 20px; background-color: rgb(235, 232, 232); border: 2px solid rgb(85, 85, 85);">\r\n<strong>Like us on Facebook:</strong><br />\r\n<div class="fb-like" data-href="https://facebook.com/itechnospot" data-width="400" data-layout="standard" data-action="like" data-show-faces="true" data-share="true"></div><br /></div></center>\r\n\r\nBefore this Admin had to hunt for the groups they admin and then go through the pending notifications and actions needed.Though the notifications of pending actions was available for then under the notifications bar but missing them may cause a havoc.And also there are many other personal notifications other than the group notifications so they had to scroll the whole of notifications to get there.Now with this feature there is a certain relief for all the group admin''s.\r\n\r\nThis problem even becomes larger when you are an admin of a group which has members in lakhs.The notification count would be more than 500+ where majority notifications will be of the groups and it was pretty difficult to find the personal and close friends notifications in the mess.So this problem is quite solved by this update.\r\n\r\nNow it is very easy to manage the group notifications efficiently and also not miss any notification from your dear ones.Finally, also if the notifications tab is categorised like Friends and Groups it would be a better complement with this new feature.But anyhow the upcoming feature will help many out there.\r\n\r\nThe Groups You Admin can be accessed by this url : <a href="https://www.facebook.com/browsegroups/?category=admin">https://www.facebook.com/browsegroups/?category=admin</a>\r\n\r\nHere are some screen shots of the new feature :\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/sc1.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1347" alt="sc1" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/sc1.png" width="178" height="56" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/sc2.png"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1348" alt="sc2" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/sc2-300x98.png" width="300" height="98" /></a>\r\n', 'Facebook adds - "Groups You Admin" under the Groups Tab', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1344'),
(1371, 1, '<h4>Micromax Canvas Doodle A111 is the first smartphone in the canvas doodle series and now that Doodle 2 and Doodle 3 have also released.But since Doodle 2 is a MediaTek device we get the CWM and Rooting tutorials faster.But anyhow the rooting tutorial is now up for Canvas Doodle A111.</h4>\r\n<h4>The phone has 3 versions of firmwares where each of these version can be rooted.But since the higher version are more secure the rooting method varies.There are basically two build versions of the OS one is 416 and the other is 428 which you get installed when you buy the phone and which can be updated to 614 version.The build versions doesn’t mean any upgrade in Android version but only some minor fixes and security updates in the existing Android 4.1.2 Jelly Bean Operating System.</h4>\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Screenshot_2014-04-27-19-47-45.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1372" alt="Screenshot_2014-04-27-19-47-45" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Screenshot_2014-04-27-19-47-45.png" width="480" height="854" /></a>\r\n<h4>How to check which build version are you running?Its very easy.Just navigate to Settings from the App Drawer then move to About Phone.There you can see the section called build number which has some information like this : Micromax_A111_V01_130614.The last three numbers denote the build which you are running.Now that you know which build you are running lets move to rooting process.</h4>\r\n<h4>Also See : How to update your Canvas Doodle to Latest Build : <a href="www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/micromax/canvas/update-canvas-doodle-a111-build-614/">www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/micromax/<strong>canvas</strong>/update-canvas-<strong>doodle</strong>-<strong>a111</strong>-build-614/</a></h4>\r\n<h3>Process 1:</h3>\r\n<h4>1.Charge your phone above 70%.</h4>\r\n<h4>2.Enable USB debugging using Settings-&gt;Developer Settings-&gt;Check USB Debugging.</h4>\r\n<h4>Now you are fine to proceed.This process is for the people who are running 416 or 428.Now they are very lucky because it can be easily rooted.They have to download an app called Framaroot which can be downloaded from this <a href="http://forum.xda-developers.com/attachment.php?attachmentid=2007672&amp;d=1370033490">link</a>.Install this app.And once the app loads select Gandalf Exploit and wait till it shows you a success message.Done now your Doodle is rooted.</h4>\r\n<h3>Process 2:</h3>\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Screenshot-from-2014-04-27-203346.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1375" alt="Screenshot from 2014-04-27 20:33:46" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Screenshot-from-2014-04-27-203346.png" width="1012" height="322" /></a>\r\n<h4>This process is for people who are running 614 version.They have to download an application called vroot which is a Chinese rooting software.But now they also have the English version of the rooting application.You can download the English version from this <a href="http://www.wuala.com/itechnospot/temp/VRoot_1.7.3.4863_english_cid1005_7337ba1e_89.exe/">link</a>.Install the application and start the application.Now switch on your USB Debugging on your phone and connect your phone.You can see that the application recognises the phone and shows you a green button called "Root".Click on that and wait till you get all the list items ticked.Once its done just reboot your phone and you are rooted.</h4>\r\nCredits:XDA,mygun.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Micromax Canvas Doodle A111 Rooting Tutorial', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1371');
