(1380, 1, '<h4>Now,you can update your Canvas Doodle A111 to the latest build version which is 614.The build version contains the main feature of FOTA(Firmware Over The Air) and the Micromax''s System Software Upgrade app is included in this update.Unlike other Micromax Smartphones this app is the same but the only difference is this app is not included in the settings panel into the About Phone unlike in other Micromax Smartphones.</h4>\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ssu.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1387" alt="ssu" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ssu.png" width="708" height="472" /></a>\r\n<h4>This build basically is just an update which includes some security fixes on which after updating is not rootable by Framaroot Application.The firmware first was seen on <a href="http://www.moulnisky.com/micromax/">http://www.moulnisky.co</a>m after which it was removed.Now moulnisky has only the 428 update.But fortunately we have downloaded the 614 before it was removed.So we have the copy of 614.</h4>\r\n<h4>Also see how to root this phone after updating :<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/android-phone/micromax-canvas-doodle-a111-rooting-tutorial/"> <span style="color: #993366;">http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/android-phone/micromax-canvas-doodle-a111-rooting-tutorial/</span></a></h4>\r\n<h4>NOTE:Before proceeding to the next step you need to backup your SMS,Call Logs,Whatsapp Conversations etc.For backup of all the installed apps you can use <span style="color: #993366;"><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=mobi.infolife.appbackup"><span style="color: #993366;">App Backup Restore</span></a></span> App.Just run the select all apps and click backup to backup all the apps.Now you have all the apps in you sdcard in a folder called App_Backup_Restore.Just take a backup of that folder before formatting.</h4>\r\n<h4>1.To begin with updating you should download the firmware update file.To download <span style="color: #993366;"><a href="https://wuala.com/adityak74/Micromax_A111/LWDEB03_2013-06-14_factory_update.zip"><span style="color: #993366;">click here</span></a>.</span></h4>\r\n<h4>2.After downloading you get the zip file : LWDEB03_2013-06-14_factory_update.zip.Now you need to have a formatted sdcard to proceed.So you can take up a sdcard which is formatted or you can copy your files in a pc and then format the sdcard.</h4>\r\n<h4>3.Now just place the downloaded zip file in the sdcard.</h4>\r\n<h4>4.To boot up into stock recovery switch off the phone.Now press and hold the volume up and the power button.After 2-3 secs you will see that Android Robot with updating progress bar appears.Now you are updating to the latest build version.This is not Android update but just some minor fixes and more stable than other versions.</h4>\r\n<h4>This version is the most stable version for Canvas Doodle A111.There is significant change in the interface though but some security fixes have been done which makes the firmware unrootable by Framaroot.</h4>\r\n<h4>Random reboots are less and also the zero RAM condition which causes the random reboot is fixed.But even then sometimes which watching YouTube videos the phone screen becomes blue for a second and reboots.</h4>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>\r\n<h4>Hardware Version</h4>\r\n</th>\r\n<th>\r\n<h4>Software Version</h4>\r\n</th>\r\n<th>\r\n<h4>Approved Date</h4>\r\n</th>\r\n<th>\r\n<h4>Release notes</h4>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>LWDM980B</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>Micromax_A111</h4>\r\n<h4>_V01_130416</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>17-04-2013</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>1st approved software</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>Micromax_A111</h4>\r\n<h4>_V01_130428</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>10-05-2013</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>1. Unable to read the Nepal SIM card contacts issue.2. Sometimes Emergency only is displayed.</h4>\r\n<h4>3. RAM zero.</h4>\r\n<h4>4. SMS not saved in message box is fixed.</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>Micromax_A111</h4>\r\n<h4>_V01_130614</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>20-06-2013</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>1. SNS(Social networking) Feature is integrated.2. FOTA is integrated.</h4>\r\n<h4>3. Sometimes Emergency Call issue is fixed.</h4>\r\n<h4>4. RAM zero issue is fixed.</h4>\r\n<h4>5. Nepal SIM Card issue is fixed.</h4>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<pre>If you have any doubts regarding installing or updating leave your comments below.</pre>\r\nCredits:moulnisky.com,wuala.com\r\n\r\nAlso See : <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/windows-phone-8-1-update-3-new-things/">http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/windows-phone-8-1-update-3-new-things/</a>', 'Update your Canvas Doodle A111 to Build 614', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1380'),
(1405, 2, 'Facebook is concerned about the privacy of their users. After adding the 2 new features to Facebook, recently:\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;1. Nearby Friends, and,\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;2. <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/facebook-adds-groups-admin-groups-tab/">Groups you Admin</a>.\r\n<strong>Sharing our personal Facebook data, with the third party apps is a serious problem for all of us.</strong><br />\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/fb1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1414" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/fb1.png" alt="Facebook Anonymous Login" /></a><br />\r\n<ol>Many apps seem to be of no use, unless you sign in with your Facebook account. But it seems that Facebook now understands this problem and has come up with a solution of ''anonymous login''. Facebook CEO, Mark Zuckerberg, stated at the company''s annual F8 conference in San Francisco,</ol>\r\n<blockquote><strong>"We know some people are scared of pressing this blue button [ Log In with Facebook button]. It''s some of the most common feedback we get on our platform... If you''re using an app that you don''t completely trust or you''re worried might spam your friends, you''re not going to give it a lot of permissions. Even if you don''t want an app to know who you are yet, you still want a streamlined process for signing in. So last year, we separated out ''read'' and ''publish'' permissions. It helped people trust the blue button and sign into apps."</strong></blockquote>\r\n\r\n<center><br /><div style="width: 450px; border-radius: 20px; background-color: rgb(235, 232, 232); border: 2px solid rgb(85, 85, 85);">\r\n<strong>Like us on Facebook:</strong><br />\r\n<div class="fb-like" data-href="https://facebook.com/itechnospot" data-width="400" data-layout="standard" data-action="like" data-show-faces="true" data-share="true"></div><br /></div></center>\r\n\r\nPeople are often concerned about granting the permission to the app to access their personal data. This feature helps the user to understand whether or whether to not give the app, the permission to access their data. It''ll be like, "try before you buy". It will help them to try apps without fear.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_1415" align="aligncenter" width="602"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/fb2.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-1415" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/fb2.png" alt="Facebook Anonymous Login-2" width="602" height="343" /></a> Facebook Anonymous Login[/caption]\r\n\r\nIn addition, another option will let you control how much advertisers see of your personal data. So, you can choose to login anonymously or semi-anonymously. For those who don’t mind sharing their information with apps and sites but want to choose exactly what those third-parties can see, Facebook also plans to unveil a line-by-line privacy control option for its regular login feature. Users could choose to share their birthday but not their friends’ list, for instance. This feature will soon be available for most of the apps.\r\n<strong>Also see: <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/mozilla-firefox-29-released-6-reasons-why-you-should-use-it/" target="neww">Mozilla releases Firefox 29: 6 reasons why you should try it</a>\r\nAnd, <a href=''http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/uncategorized/google-glass-new-channel-money-transfer/''>Google Glass, a new channel for Money Transfer ?</a></strong>', 'Facebook launches new feature: "Anonymous Login"', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1405'),
(1429, 2, '<strong>Mozilla has recently released Firefox 29</strong> which has a completely different interface and has customizable menu and a redesigned synchronization feature. Here are some reasons why you should try this browser...\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>Improvised User Interface</strong>\r\nThe block view of the tabs of Firefox 28 is now gone. The new ''Australis'' (name given to the design) design of Firefox 29 now has its tabs, sleek and curved. This feature is the most noticeable as soon as you start the browser. Thus, this browser now resembles Google Chrome. Also, the non active tabs are made translucent, so that the active tab is more highlighted and the distraction is reduced. \r\n<br />\r\n[caption id="attachment_1433" align="aligncenter" width="868"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/7.jpg"><img src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/7.jpg" alt="Firefox 29 Tabs" width="868" height="688" class="size-full wp-image-1433" /></a> Firefox 29 Tabs[/caption]\r\n<br />\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>Menu Position</strong>\r\nThe orange menu present at the top-left corner in Firefox 28 is now not there in Firefox 29. It has been customized to be included in the toolbar itself. The menu includes options for saving the page directly, open a new window, private browsing, options, home page button, group your tabs, preferences, etc.\r\n<br />\r\n[caption id="attachment_1432" align="aligncenter" width="270"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/FirefoxPortable21.png"><img src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/FirefoxPortable21.png" alt="Firefox 28 Menu" width="270" height="290" class="size-full wp-image-1432" /></a> Firefox 28 Menu[/caption]\r\n<br />\r\n[caption id="attachment_1437" align="aligncenter" width="580"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/2.jpg"><img src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/2-1024x545.jpg" alt="Firefox 29 Menu" width="580" height="308" class="size-large wp-image-1437" /></a> Firefox 29 Menu[/caption]\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Also see, <a href=''http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/uncategorized/google-glass-new-channel-money-transfer/''>Google Glass, a new channel for Money Transfer ?</a></strong>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>Customizablity</strong>\r\nWithin the new menu, there is a button saying ''Customize''. On clicking this button, we can change the positions of our buttons that we want to be a part of our navigation toolbar. This also includes repositioning or removing the search field. You can customize this menu to keep the buttons that you use frequently, on your toolbar, right in front of you, so that you need not click on the menu and search for the required button every time.\r\n<br />\r\n[caption id="attachment_1438" align="aligncenter" width="504"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/FirefPortable2.png"><img src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/FirefPortable2.png" alt="Firefox 29 Customized Menu " width="504" height="611" class="size-full wp-image-1438" /></a> Firefox 29 Customized Menu [/caption]\r\n<br />\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>Easy Access to Add-ons Manager</strong>\r\n\r\n<center><br /><div style="width: 450px; border-radius: 20px; background-color: rgb(235, 232, 232); border: 2px solid rgb(85, 85, 85);">\r\n<strong>Like us on Facebook:</strong><br />\r\n<div class="fb-like" data-href="https://facebook.com/itechnospot" data-width="400" data-layout="standard" data-action="like" data-show-faces="true" data-share="true"></div><br /></div></center>\r\n\r\nFirefox includes an Add-ons Manager that you can access directly from the menu. If you are using this button frequently, then you can also put it near the url bar, i.e. on the navigation toolbar. It helps you easily install new add-ons.\r\n<br />\r\n[caption id="attachment_1443" align="aligncenter" width="580"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/4.jpg"><img src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/4-1024x546.jpg" alt="Firefox 29 Add-ons" width="580" height="309" class="size-large wp-image-1443" /></a> Firefox 29 Add-ons[/caption]\r\n<br />\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>Easy Bookmarks</strong>\r\nManaging the bookmarks is made easy in Firefox 29. A bookmark manager icon is now found within the navigation bar, next to the star icon that is used to bookmark pages. The new icon highlights users'' bookmarks more prominently. Finding and managing bookmarks is now easier than that in Firefox 28.\r\n<br />\r\n[caption id="attachment_1441" align="aligncenter" width="231"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/bookmark1.gif"><img src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/bookmark1.gif" alt="Firefox 29 Bookmarks" width="231" height="61" class="size-full wp-image-1441" /></a> Firefox 29 Bookmarks[/caption]\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Also see: <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/facebook-launches-new-feature-anonymous-login/" target="newwindow">Facebook launches new feature: “Anonymous Login”</a>\r\nAnd: <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/windows-phone-8-1-update-3-new-things/" target="new">Windows Phone 8.1 Update – 3 New Things</a><br /></strong>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>Synchronization</strong>\r\nFirefox 29 has focused on improving the synchronization service and hence it has come up with this Advanced Firefox Sync Service. This feature makes it possible for users to easily transfer their Firefox features, including their settings, their history, their bookmarks and more, from one device to another. By creating a Firefox account, users can transfer their features from computer to computer or to the mobile, Android version of Firefox. \r\n<br />\r\n[caption id="attachment_1445" align="aligncenter" width="216"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/sync.jpg"><img src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/sync-216x300.jpg" alt="Firefox 29 Sync" width="216" height="300" class="size-medium wp-image-1445" /></a> Firefox 29 Sync[/caption]\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nTo try out this new browser, you can <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/" target="new_window_1">Download it</a> from here. Let me know your experience about Firefox 29. I would love to hear it from my readers, keep commenting!!', 'Mozilla releases Firefox 29: 6 reasons why you should try it', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1429'),
(1469, 2, '[caption id="attachment_1483" align="aligncenter" width="580"]<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Google_Glass_Explorer_Edition.jpeg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1483" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Google_Glass_Explorer_Edition-1024x574.jpeg" alt="Google Glass" width="580" height="325" /></a> Google Glass[/caption]\r\n\r\nGoogle Glass has already started attracting the users because of its simple, easy to access features. This completely new device, has excited developers all over the world, to come and develop programs for Google Glass. The best feature of this Glass is that it''s hands-free, intelligent and be used by the users as ''<strong>wearable computing</strong>'' eyeware. Operating this Glass, is very simple; voice-commands. Equipped with a smartphone like display, wifi and bluetooth connectivity, it is powered by the <strong>Android Mobile Operating System</strong>.\r\n\r\nYou can watch the following video, which describes how <strong>simple and fascinating</strong>, it is to use a Google Glass.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/4EvNxWhskf8" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></center>There are many applications that have been developed on Google Glass. You can <a href="http://glass-apps.org/google-glass-application-list">find a list of applications here.</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Also see: <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/facebook-launches-new-feature-anonymous-login/">Facebook launches new feature: “Anonymous Login”</a></strong>\r\n\r\nGoogle is working on programming this Glass to transfer Money. Once done, this might become the most easiest way to transfer money. Just a few taps, a few swipes and a few voice commands, and the money will be transferred. Google is going to introduce, Google Wallet whereby users can use their voices to ask the Glass to transfer money just by saying, <strong>''Send Money''</strong>. According to Google, sending money using your Google Wallet balance or you bank account linked to Google Wallet is free. But if you send dough via your credit or debit card, there''s a 2.9 percent transaction fee or 30 cents -- whichever is higher.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<div style="width: 450px; border-radius: 20px; background-color: #ebe8e8; border: 2px solid #555555;"><strong>Like us on Facebook:</strong></div>\r\n</center>\r\n<div class="fb-like" data-href="https://facebook.com/itechnospot" data-width="400" data-layout="standard" data-action="like" data-show-faces="true" data-share="true"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHave a look at the <strong>Google Wallet</strong>:\r\n\r\n<center><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/VuFVsaFCzsw" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></center><i>Reference: <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2014/05/05/google-wallet-is-coming-to-glass/?ncid=rss">Techcrunch</a></i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Also see, <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/technology-2/mozilla-firefox-29-released-6-reasons-why-you-should-use-it/">Mozilla releases Firefox 29: 6 reasons why you should try it</a></strong>', 'Google Glass, a new channel for Money Transfer ?', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1469'),
