(1528, 1, '<h4>Moto E sold out even more faster than you expected and we hope you are waiting for the smartphone to come back in stock on Flipkart.Its a good new for all!!Moto E is back again in stock <strong>From 11 am,23rd</strong> May.Stock are limited to 20,000 units and we hope that the stock will be again over in one hour or so as soon as the selling starts.</h4>\r\n<h4>We have already reviewed<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/motorola/motorola-launches-moto-e-on-flipkart/"> Moto E for features and specs.</a>Moto E is also a great budget killer smartphone under the 10k line-up in India and already many people have it delivered from Flipkart.</h4>\r\n<h4>Today Micromax has launched a new device called Micromax Unite 2 A106 which will compete with the <a href="http://bit.ly/QGBQcU">Moto E</a> and <a href="http://bit.ly/1lsNTTC">Lava Iris 406q</a> in the 7k price bracket.</h4>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/a106.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1533" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/a106.png" alt="a106" width="480" height="369" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>The device is officially listed on the <a href="http://www.micromaxinfo.com/mobiles/smartphones/canvas/Unite-2-A106">Micromax Official Site.</a></h4>\r\n<h4>Micromax Canvas Unite 2 A106 runs Android Kitkat 4.4.2 out of the box with 1.3 GHz Mediatek MT6582M chipset and Mali-400MP2 GPU @ 416 MHz.A106 is priced at Rs.6999/-.At this price bracket this is the first Micromax phone running Kitkat and is also a Quad-Core smartphone.Interesting is the RAM.While we are seeing all budget devices having 1GB of RAM and this one is also not far behind.This one also sports 4,7 inch  WVGA IPS display with a resolution of 480 X 800.T<span style="color: #3e3e3e;">he handset utilizes a Bright Graph IPS panel that can deliver exceptional viewing angles and superior color contrast and brightness..</span>The storage is expandable upto 32gb and you also get the 3G dual SIM support,Bluetooth 4.0,WiFi and USB.The  primary camera is 5MP Auto Focus with LED flash and the front facing camera is 2MP.The battery is 2000mAh which is fair enough to power this display and the chipset for a day of regular usage.It comes with a Motion sensor and a Proximity Sensor.</h4>\r\n<h4><span style="color: #444444;">Among other specifications, the phone runs on Android 4.4 KitKat and comes with support for 20 Indian regional languages like Hindi, Gujarati, Punjabi, Malayalam, Tamil, Telugu, Kannada, Odia, Bengali, Assamese, Marathi, Nepali, Bodo, Dogri, Konkani, Kashmiri, Maithili, Manipuri, Sanskrit and Sindhi.</span></h4>\r\n<h3 style="color: #3e3e3e;">Key Specs</h3>\r\n<table style="color: #3e3e3e;" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Model</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Micromax Unite 2(A106)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Display</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">4.7 inch, 480×800 WVGA</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Processor</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">1.3 GHz Quad Core</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">RAM</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">1 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Internal Storage</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">4 GB, Expandable up to 32 GB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">OS</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Android 4.4.2 KitKat</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Camera</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">5 MP (Primary)/ 2 MP(Secondary)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Battery</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">2,000 mAh</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Price</td>\r\n<td valign="top" width="295">Rs 6,999</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3 style="color: #3e3e3e;">Now you have to decide for yourself whether you will go with Moto E or Micromax Unite 2.Comment your views.</h3>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Comment your views about the Micromax Unite 2 and Moto E.Which one do you think will be a success?</span></h4>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Moto E Up for grabs again,Micromax A106 launched with Android Kitkat', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1528'),
(1545, 1, 'After the <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/smartphones/micromax/canvas/moto-e-grabs-againmicromax-a106-launched-android-kitkat/" target="_blank">Micromax Canvas Unite 2</a> which we saw yesterday we have one more smartphone spotted which could surely beat the Moto E sales in India.This is also a quad core phone running Android Kitkat 4.4.The expected price of this device is expected to be much lower than Unite 2 and will be around 6k.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Micromax-Canvas-Enagage-A091-Box-Image.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1546" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Micromax-Canvas-Enagage-A091-Box-Image.jpg" alt="Micromax-Canvas-Enagage-A091-Box-Image" width="395" height="531" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Micromax-Canvas-Engage-Back-Box-Listed-Specifications.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1547" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Micromax-Canvas-Engage-Back-Box-Listed-Specifications.jpg" alt="Micromax-Canvas-Engage-Back-Box-Listed-Specifications" width="413" height="574" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe phone features 4 inch WVGA display with 1.2 GHz Quad Core with 512 MB of RAM and is running the latest Android Kitkat 4.4.Internal storage is 4GB as seen in the mid range phones.It is also capable of recording and playing HD videos.The battery is 1500mAh and gives talktime upto 5.5hrs.The phone has a 5MP rear and 0.3MP front camera.It is a dual SIM phone with WiFi,Bluetooth and GPS.\r\n\r\nKey Specs:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4 inch <span class="hiddenSpellError">WVGA</span> screen.</li>\r\n	<li>1.2GHz Quad core processor.</li>\r\n	<li><span class="hiddenSpellError">512MP</span> RAM, 4GB ROM.</li>\r\n	<li><span class="hiddenSpellError">15000mAh</span> battery.</li>\r\n	<li><span class="hiddenSpellError">5MP</span> Rear &amp; 0.3MP front camera.</li>\r\n	<li>Android 4.4.2 Kitkat operating system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://micromaxcanvas.co.in/mmx-enagage-a091-specs-kitkat-phone/" target="_blank">Source</a>', 'Micromax Canvas Engage A091 with Android 4.4.2 Kitkat OS', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1545'),
(1552, 5, 'The 3 operating systems which i booted into my laptop are\r\n\r\nWindows 7 ultimate\r\n\r\nUbuntu 14.04 LTS (unity)\r\n\r\nKali Linux 1.0.6\r\n\r\nThe specs of my laptop are core 2 duo processor with 1.5 GHz, 1gb ram, 160gb hard disk and yeah of course its 32 bit.\r\n\r\nThe reason why I disclosed these specs is to convince you of the fact that, if my laptop can be loaded with 3 operating systems then, so can yours.\r\n\r\nInitially my laptop was loaded with windows 7.\r\n\r\nI then proceeded to install Ubuntu 14.04 by imaging the Ubuntu iso on by usb using linuxlive.\r\n\r\nLinuxlive is an excellent software and its usage can be easily googled, so let me skip that part lest it will increase the length of the story.\r\n\r\nHence I downloaded the software and successfully completed in imaging it. Now I tried to install it using usb, alas I encountered a problem whenever I selected the option to install ubuntu along with windows my laptop rebooted and the whole process went into a loop. It took me sometime to realise that I did not have any logical drives and somehow figured this is causing the loop. Of course I could have went for manual partitioning but all the mount point, file system,,etc freaked me out.\r\n\r\nI then proceeded to install another software titled easeus partition master, whose usage can again be googled. Easeus partition master can be used to convert logical to primary and vice versa in addition to modifying partitions. This solved my bootloop problem and installation was completed successfully.\r\n\r\nI then did the same for kali linux, the problem with kali was its version (1.0.6) was not compatible with linuxlive although it tried its best to image by considering the parameters of the previous version (1.0.5) and it succeeded.\r\n\r\nWhen I tried to install it with an usb, made bootable by linuxlive it couldn’t find the firmware for wifi driver. I then found another imaging software win32diskimager from kali linux’s official website. Again I encountered the primary drive problem disguised in another way which can be solved using the same steps as above.\r\n\r\nMoral: whatever problem you encounter while doing something, just don’t give up as there is always an alternative thing or alternative method to do that thing. :D\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n\r\nUbuntu 14.04 and kali Linux requires a logical drive to install. If you have only primary drives (now don’t ask me the meaning of primary and logical coz even I don’t have an in-depth knowledge) and proceed to install Ubuntu, then you will find yourself in a troublesome situation wherein you will find the Ubuntu installation going into a loop(it happened for me).\r\n\r\nYou can try manual partition in ubuntu if you are the adventurous or programming type. For others I would suggest you to use Easeus partition master.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou can convert only certain no of partitions to primary even by using Easeus as windows is capable of having a max of 3 such drives.\r\n\r\nWhen you delete a logical drive the memory becomes freespace whereas if you delete a primary drive it becomes an unallocated space.\r\n\r\nAlways start deleting parititions from the rightmost position in disk management. If you delete some partitions in the middle it may have an effect on the partitions to the right of it.', 'The story of how I triple booted my laptop', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1552'),
(1567, 1, '<p style="color: #525253;">India joins the league of major mobile services markets across the globe featuring their own mobile device brands to leverage the phenomenal rise in the demand for these devices. According to Counterpoint Technology Research, an independent market research and consulting firm, their latest research from the Market Monitor program showed that two-thirds of the total mobile phone shipments and over half of the smartphone shipments for India is attributable to local brands. Canalys, another analysis company, reported a <a style="color: #12768e;" href="http://www.policychargingcontrol.com/mobile-devices-and-wearables-trends/2075-xiaomi-beats-samsung-in-china-s-smartphone-market-with-14-in-market-share-canalysis">similar situation in China</a>, where 8 out of the 10 top smartphone vendors in the country are local vendors.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #525253;">Counterpoint said that the smartphone market in India grew by 68% in the last year, though demand for its predecessor, the feature phone, fell by 16% in the last quarter. According to Counterpoint, Micromax, India''s own brand, came out top in the overall phone segment and the feature phone segment, and second after Samsung, in the smartphone segment with a market share of 16.6%, 15.2% and 19.1% respectively for the last quarter. Other players in the handset segment are Karbonn, Motorola, Celkon, Nokia, Apple, Sony and Lava. By taking over top global brands such as Nokia and Samsung, Micromax is set to dominate the India mobile market in a big way, and is already the world''s 10th largest supplier of mobile phones in terms of volume, added Canalys.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #525253;">Since Micromax if offering what the consumers in India wanted the users are increasing day by day.Micromax has been launching low-cost budget smartphones with excellent specs which makes users in India to buy their products.Also it has shown a competitive and aggressive marketing for other OEMs like Motorola and Xiaomi for entering into the budget bracket of Indian market.As report says Micromax clearly leads the way.It has also officially partnered with Google for the Android One project of low cost nexus-like devices for the 6 million users in India and other Asian countries.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #525253;">According to Counterpoint, the trend, both in India and China shows the onset of more intensified competition in the mobile device space, specifically the smartphone segment with Asian OEMs such as Xiaomi, Gionee, Huawei and Asus laying out aggressive plans to venture abroad and capitalize on the demand for competitively-prices, premium smartphones. More information on the research is available <a style="color: #12768e;" href="http://www.counterpointresearch.com/2q2014marketmonitorindia">here.</a></p>', 'Micromax Overtakes Samsung and Nokia,now the Major Phone Brand in India', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1567'),
(1570, 1, '<h2 class="short-teaser" style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #0000ff;">Micromax is gearing up to release its budget octa-core device this independence day.</span></h2>\r\n<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden" style="color: #222222;">\r\n<div class="field-items" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">\r\n<div class="field-item even" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">Micromax is looking to emphasise on its Indian roots with an upcoming smartphone centered around the country’s independence day. Rather dramatically titled, the Micromax Unite Anthem, it is scheduled to be released independence day.</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;"><strong style="font-style: inherit;">Specifications</strong></p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">@MMXNewscaster had revealed details about an upcoming handset back in July. According to the tipster, the Unite Anthem will come with a 1.4 GHz octa-core processor paired with 1 GB of RAM.</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">It will have support for two SIMs working simultaneously and will run Android 4.4 KitKat out of the box.</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">The Unite Anthem A290 is tipped to have 8 GB of internal memory which can be expanded further via a microSD card.</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">On the optics front, the Unite Anthem A290 boasts of an 8 megapixel primary camera and a 5 megapixel front camera.</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;"><strong style="font-style: inherit;">Price and Release Date</strong></p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;"><a style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #004a6b;" href="http://www.gizbot.com/mobile/micromax-unite-anthem-a290-august-15-launch-octa-core-india-news-mobile-018772.html" target="_blank">Gizbot</a> reached out to its sources and has confirmed that the budget octa-core smartphone will indeed be unveiled on Friday, August 15th.</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">The company also did a bit of digging around on Zauba, which tracks the import and export of goods in the country. The website revealed that close to 17,000 units have been imported of the A290 this week at the cost of Rs. 7,056. Going by this, it is fair to say that the Unite Anthem A290 is likely to cost close to Rs. 10,000.</p>\r\n<p style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">The import price is around 7k but it will hit the market at approx price of 10k.If you want to buy for less than 10k you need to wait for the device to get listed in e-commerce websites.Till then keep waiting for the device to launch on the Independence day.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Micromax Unite Anthem A290 specifications, price and release date', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1570'),
(1575, 1, 'Micromax seems all set to launch the octa-core Canvas Knight Cameo A290 smartphone in India soon, if claims by an established retailer from Mumbai, and a listing by an online retailer, are any indication.\r\n\r\nClaiming current availability along with a price of Rs. 12,499, mobile retailer Mahesh Telecom has further <a style="color: #006699;" href="https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10152195595841104" target="_blank">listed</a> the specifications of the unannounced<a style="color: #006699;" href="http://gadgets.ndtv.com/micromax-canvas-knight-cameo-1857">Micromax Canvas Knight Cameo A290</a> along with an image on its <a style="color: #006699;" href="http://gadgets.ndtv.com/tags/facebook">Facebook</a>page. The retailer has also <a style="color: #006699;" href="https://twitter.com/MAHESHTELECOM/status/499858418018947072" target="_blank">tweeted</a> saying, "#Micromax Canvas Knight Camera A290, now available for Rs. 12,499 only."\r\n\r\nIt''s worth noting that we are yet to hear an official announcement from<a style="color: #006699;" href="http://gadgets.ndtv.com/mobiles/micromax-phones">Micromax</a> about the device.\r\n\r\nAccording to the specifications listed by Mahesh Telecom, the dual-SIM Micromax Canvas Knight Cameo A290 will run <a style="color: #006699;" href="http://gadgets.ndtv.com/android">Android</a> 4.4.2 KitKat out-of-the-box, and feature a 4.7-inch HD (720x1280 pixels) display.\r\n\r\nWhile the Mumbai retailer notes the Canvas Knight Cameo A290 smartphone packs a true octa-core processor coupled with 1GB of RAM, the clock-speed speed was not revealed. The smartphone is said to sport an 8-megapixel autofocus rear camera with LED flash, while there is a 5-megapixel front-facing camera also onboard. The 8GB of inbuilt storage on the Canvas Knight Cameo A290 is said to be expandable up to 32GB (via microSD card).\r\n\r\nAs mentioned earlier, the Micromax Canvas Knight Cameo A290 smartphone has already been <a style="color: #006699;" href="http://www.snapdeal.com/product/micromax-canvas-knight-cameo-a290/1100462602" target="_blank">listed</a> by an online retailer at Rs. 12,777.\r\n\r\nThe Canvas Knight Cameo A290 specifications listed by the Mumbai retailer match those listed by Snapdeal, which however additionally adds a 1.4GHz clock-speed for the octa-core processor, and a 2010mAh battery capacity, both details that were missed by the Mumbai-based retailer. Connectivity options on the Micromax Canvas Knight Cameo A290 smartphone include 3G, GPRS/ EDGE, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Bluetooth 4.0, and GPS.\r\n\r\n<strong><a style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000;">KEY SPECS</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">Display : 4.70-inch</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">Processor : 1.4GHz</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">Front Camera : 5-megapixel</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">Resolution : 720x1280 pixels</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">RAM : 1GB</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">OS : Android 4.4</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">Storage : 8GB</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">Rear Camera : 8-megapixel</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong style="color: #4b4b4b;">Battery capacity : 2010mAh</strong></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Micromax Canvas Knight Cameo Now Available Online at Rs. 12,777', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1575'),
(1581, 1, 'One more day, one more piece of bad news for Windows Phone: IDC found that in the second quarter of 2014, Windows Phone''s market share dropped yet again, to well under 3%. Is it time to sound taps for the operating system?\r\n\r\nThere''s only bad news in the IDC report. In the second quarter of 2014, <a href="http://www.idc.com/getdoc.jsp?containerId=prUS25037214">IDC says that Windows Phone had a 2.5% market share</a>, down from 3.4% a year ago. Even worse is that the total number of phones shipped dropped as well, even while the smartphone market continues to have sizzling growth. IDC says there were 7.4 million Windows Phones shipped in the quarter, compared to 8.2 million in the same quarter a year ago. That drop happened at the same time that total smartphone shipments grew from 240.5 million in the second quarter of 2013 to 301.3 million in the second quarter of 2014, for 25.3% growth.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://blogs.computerworld.com/sites/computerworld.com/files/u98/idc_2014_third_quarter.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\nThese latest IDC numbers <a href="http://blogs.computerworld.com/windows-phone/24202/windows-phone-continues-slide-now-under-3-share-worldwide-it-finally-dead">almost precisely mirror the most recent ones by Strategy Analytics.</a> Strategy Analytics found that in the second quarter, Windows Phone had a 2.7% market share, down from 3.8% a year previously. <a href="https://bgr.com/2014/07/31/android-vs-ios-vs-windows-phone-vs-blackberry/">It also found that total sales dropped to 8 million in the quarter</a>, from to 8.9 million in the same quarter a year ago.\r\n\r\nEven in a traditional Microsoft stronghold people are staying away from Windows Phone: Good Technology''s most recent Mobility Index Report <a href="http://blogs.computerworld.com/windows-phone/24249/enterprises-windows-phone-drop-dead">found Windows Phone with a mere 1% of enterprise market share</a> for smartphones.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, IDC found that Android continues to dominate smartphone sales, with 84.7% market share in the second quarter, compared to 79.6% a year previously. The iPhone had 11.7% in the second quarter, compared to 13% a year previously.\r\n\r\nIf you look hard -- and you have to look really hard -- you can find some glimmers of hope for Windows Phone. IDC said that Microsoft <a href="http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9250385/The_news_isn_t_good_for_Windows_Phone"> might be signing up more manufacturing partners</a> for the second half of 2014. And Paul Thurrott points out that Microsoft now <a href="http://winsupersite.com/windows-phone/its-too-early-write-third-smartphone-ecosystem">gives away Windows Phone licenses for free to Windows Phone makers</a>, which could bring in even more partners, and drop the prices of Windows Phones.\r\n\r\nWindows Phone does best among bargain hunters, IDC notes -- just over 60% of all Windows Phone devices sold are $200 or below, not including contract incentives. So new manufacturers selling low-cost phones could eventually boost Windows Phone sales.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately for Microsoft, though, Android is strongest at the low end as well, with almost 60% of its sales going towards under-$200 phones. Still, it''s not quite time to say Windows Phone is dead. But if a year from now it''s still bouncing along the bottom, you can kiss it good-bye.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blogs.computerworld.com/windows-phone/24263/windows-phones-nosedive-continues-when-will-it-rip">Source</a>', 'Windows Phone''s : When will it R.I.P.?', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1581'),
(1584, 1, 'Google Inc is buying JetPac Inc, the startup that designs social travel applications disclosed on its website on Friday, without providing details.\r\n\r\n"We''ll be removing Jetpac''s apps from the App Store in the coming days, and ending support for them on 9/15," stated a posting on JetPac''s homepage. (http://bit.ly/1b66Re9)\r\n\r\nSan Francisco-based JetPac has created a mobile application that uses pictures from various social networking sites to create city guides.\r\n\r\nEarlier this year, Google bought Nest Labs Inc, which makes smart thermostat and smoke alarms, for $3.2 billion, making the deal one of the largest in Google''s history.\r\n\r\nGoogle was not available for comment outside of normal business hours.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Google Buys : JetPac - A City-Guide App Maker', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1584'),
(1587, 1, '<span style="line-height: 1.6;">Yahoo on Thursday announced the launch of the new Yahoo Mail app for iOS and Android users in India. The app is designed to allow users to access mail as well as information important to them, all in one space.</span>\r\n\r\nThe app will bring together the information users need every day, such as email, news, weather and more - and let them access it all in one place.\r\n\r\nYahoo says that the app is designed with focus on simplicity. So the experience of the app is similar to the Yahoo Mail experience, but with a one-tap access to personalized, real-time information.\r\n\r\nThe app opens into the Yahoo Mail inbox with icons for Mail, News and Today. On Android, swiping to the left or right of the screen will let the user move between their inbox, news stream, and Today.\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 300px; height: 540px;" src="http://static.dnaindia.com/sites/default/files/2014/08/14/259406-sgprandroidmail-cards-3-flickr-1.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\nThe News icon will bring the latest developments in politics, business and entertainment in a ''visually rich'' news stream.\r\n\r\nThe Today icon will have a snapshot of information important to the user, from a news digest to local weather to images from Flickr.\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 600px; height: 432px;" src="http://static.dnaindia.com/sites/default/files/2014/08/14/259405-inpripadmail-3cards-1-weather.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\nAs part of this update, Yahoo is also introducing a new search option in the inbox which allows users to search for both people and messages. The app filters search results by messages, files or photos, and users can easily scroll through them to find what they are looking for.\r\n\r\nThe latest version of Yahoo Mail for iOS and Android phones can be downloaded from the App Store and Google Play, respectively.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.dnaindia.com/scitech/report-yahoo-announces-launch-of-its-new-mail-app-in-india-2010816">Source</a>', 'Yahoo announces launch of its new mail app in India', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1587');
