(1641, 1, '<span style="font-size: 18px;">\r\nIn operations research <b>Johnson''s rule</b> is a method of scheduling jobs in two work centers. Its primary objective is to find an optimal sequence of jobs to reduce makespan (the total amount of time it takes to complete all jobs). It also reduces the number of idle time between the two work centers. The method minimizes the makespan in the case of two work centers. Furthermore, the method finds the shortest makespan in the case of three work centers if additional constrains are met.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">The technique requires several preconditions:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The time for each job must be constant.</li>\r\n	<li>Job times must be mutually exclusive of the job sequence.</li>\r\n	<li>All jobs must go through first work center before going through the second work center.</li>\r\n	<li>There must be no job priorities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">Johnson''s rule is as follows:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>List the jobs and their times at each work center.</li>\r\n	<li>Select the job with the shortest activity time. If that activity time is for the first work center, then schedule the job first. If that activity time is for the second work center then schedule the job last. Break ties arbitrarily.</li>\r\n	<li>Eliminate the shortest job from further consideration.</li>\r\n	<li>Repeat steps 2 and 3, working towards the center of the job schedule until all jobs have been scheduled.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<iframe src="http://www.flipkart.com/affiliate/displayWidget?affrid=WRID-139426617008484357" width="740" height="100" frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">Given significant idle time at the second work center (from waiting for the job to be finished at the first work center), job splitting may be used.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">Each of five jobs needs to go through work center A and B. Find the optimum sequence of jobs using Johnson''s rule.</span>\r\n<table><caption><span style="font-size: 18px;">Job times (hours)</span></caption>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Job</th>\r\n<th>Work center A</th>\r\n<th>Work center B</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>A</td>\r\n<td>3.2</td>\r\n<td>4.2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>B</td>\r\n<td>4.7</td>\r\n<td>1.5</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>C</td>\r\n<td>2.2</td>\r\n<td>5.0</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>D</td>\r\n<td>5.8</td>\r\n<td>4.0</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>E</td>\r\n<td>3.1</td>\r\n<td>2.8</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">1. The smallest time is located in Job B (1.50 hours). Since the time is in Work Center B, schedule this job last. Eliminate Job B from further consideration.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class="wikitable">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td>B</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">2. The next smallest time is located in Job C (2.20 hours). Since the time is in Work Center A, schedule this job first. Eliminate Job C from further consideration.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class="wikitable">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>C</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td>B</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">3. The next smallest time after that is located in Job E (2.80 hours). Since the time is in Work Center B, schedule this job last. Eliminate Job E from further consideration.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class="wikitable">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>C</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td>E</td>\r\n<td>B</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">4. The next smallest time after is located in Job A (3.20 hours). Since the time is in Work Center A, schedule this job first. Eliminate Job A from further consideration.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class="wikitable">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>C</td>\r\n<td>A</td>\r\n<td> ?</td>\r\n<td>E</td>\r\n<td>B</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<iframe src="http://www.flipkart.com/affiliate/displayWidget?affrid=WRID-139426330076671480" width="728" height="90" frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">5. The only job left to consider is Job D.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class="wikitable">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>C</td>\r\n<td>A</td>\r\n<td>D</td>\r\n<td>E</td>\r\n<td>B</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">The code for the Algorithm is available in the Github repo link below </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="color: #0000ff;">[sociallocker]<a style="color: #0000ff;" href="https://github.com/adicsarch/JhonsonJobSequencing">JhonsonJobSequencing</a>.[/sociallocker]</span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 18px;">And live demo of the Algorithm is <span style="color: #0000ff;"><a style="color: #0000ff;" href="http://www.itechnospot.com/jobseq/">here</a>.</span></span>', 'Jhonson''s Job Sequencing Algorithm', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1641'),
(1657, 1, 'Xtreme Download Manager is a powerful tool to increase download speed up-to 500%, resume broken/dead downloads, capture FLV videos from any site and schedule downloads.Many of us always try to find out alternate to our very own favourite download manager Internet Download Manager which is only available for windows.Now here is the IDM look alike XDMAN : Xtreme Download Manager.\r\n\r\nOne good thing about this software is this a software based on Java 6 SE which makes this software a cross platfrom product now you can also use this in your Windows.\r\n\r\nHere are some key features to look at:\r\n\r\n<b>Key features:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Extreme download acceleration. (up to 32 segments per download, connection re-use, data compression)</li>\r\n	<li>Integration with almost every browser available, including Google Chrome,Firefox, Internet explorer, Opera, Safari, SeaMonkey or any other browser/application using advanced browser integration.</li>\r\n	<li>Capture flv,webm(html5),mp4,avi and many other video formats from numerous sites like YouTube, Metacafe, Dailymotion, Vimeo etc with XDM media grabber.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to refresh dead/broken/invalid download links (caused by session-expiration) using refresh link option.</li>\r\n	<li>Scheduling, virus scanning, auto shutdown, batch download, clipboard monitoring,drag and drop etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to run within corporate firewall as XDM supports automatic proxy configuration scripts, proxy authentication (NTLM,Digest,Kerberos,Spengo), installation without admin rights. Currently only one commercial download manager supports these features.</li>\r\n	<li>Supports HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, redirection, cookies, authentication (including Windows ISA ), password management etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<address>XDM is a superfast, add free, open source download manager.</address><address>Author: Subhra Das Gupta</address><address>Powered By: Java</address><address>Components:</address>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><address>XDM core (Java)</address></li>\r\n	<li><address>XDM Firefox integration (JavaScript/XPCOM)</address></li>\r\n	<li><address>Network configuration utility for Windows (WinInet/VC++)</address></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAre you a developer?Want to check out the source?Here it is <a href="http://sourceforge.net/p/xdman/code/ref/master/">Source.</a>No a developer try installing it.Steps to install <a href="http://xdman.sourceforge.net/download.html">here</a>.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>Installing on Linux :</h3>\r\n1.Download the xdman_mint_ubuntu.deb file from <a href="http://xdman.sourceforge.net/xdman_mint_ubuntu.deb">here</a>.\r\n\r\n2.To install this debian package file : Open terminal and type :- sudo dpkg -i xdman_mint_ubuntu.deb.\r\n\r\n3.If you get permissions error make sure you make the .deb file executable.To make this while in terminal type : sudo chmod a+x xdman_mint_ubuntu.deb\r\n\r\n4.Install and enjoy.Integrate the XDMAN to browser from the popup when you first use it.</blockquote>\r\n<h2>For Developers :</h2>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>To get the source code :</h3>\r\n1.Open terminal : Make sure you have git installed if yes skip this step else type : sudo apt-get install git and press enter to install git.\r\n\r\n2.Then type this command : git clone http://git.code.sf.net/p/xdman/code xdman-code\r\n\r\nEnjoy the XDM and thanks to Subhra Das Gupta for developing it!!!</blockquote>', 'XDMAN : Alternate to IDM for Linux', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1657'),
(1665, 1, '<p>Finally after a long wait leaks and all those anticipating blog posts on different leak websites here is the next verision of Android 5.0 Lollipop as many sites suggested the name would be.</p>\r\n<p>[embed]http://www.android.com/new/videos/tangible_interactions.webm[/embed]</p>\r\n<p>Here are some quick features what Android 5.0 L has to offer :</p>\r\n<div class="content-wrapper">\r\n<div class="collapse js-accordion is-active" data-accordion-name="features">\r\n<ul class="container feature-list">\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Material Design</h3>\r\n<p>A bold, colorful, and responsive UI design for consistent, intuitive experiences across all your devices</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Responsive, natural motion, realistic lighting and shadows, and familiar visual elements make it easier to navigate your device</li>\r\n<li>Vivid new colors, typography, and edge-to-edge imagery help to focus your attention</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Notifications</h3>\r\n<p>New ways to control when and how you receive messages - only get interrupted when you want to be</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>View and respond to messages directly from your lock screen. Includes the ability to hide sensitive content for these notifications</li>\r\n<li>For fewer disruptions, turn on Priority mode via your device’s volume button so only certain people and notifications get through. Or schedule recurring downtime like 10pm to 8am when only Priority notifications can get through</li>\r\n<li>With Lollipop, incoming phone calls won’t interrupt what you’re watching or playing. You can choose to answer the call or just keep doing what you’re doing</li>\r\n<li>Control the notifications triggered by your apps; hide sensitive content and prioritize or turn off the app’s notifications entirely</li>\r\n<li>More intelligent ranking of notifications based on who they’re from and the type of communication. See all your notifications in one place by tapping the top of the screen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Battery</h3>\r\n<p>Power for the long haul</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A battery saver feature which extends device use by up to 90 mins</li>\r\n<li>Estimated time left to fully charge is displayed when your device is plugged in</li>\r\n<li>Estimated time left on your device before you need to charge again can now be found in battery settings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Security</h3>\r\n<p>Keep your stuff safe and sound</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New devices come with encryption automatically turned on to help protect data on lost or stolen devices</li>\r\n<li>SELinux enforcing for all applications means even better protection against vulnerabilities and malware</li>\r\n<li>Use Android Smart Lock to secure your phone or tablet by pairing it with a trusted device like your wearable or even your car</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Device Sharing</h3>\r\n<p>More flexible sharing with family and friends</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Multiple users for phones. If you forget your phone, you still can call any of your friends (or access any of your messages, photos etc.) by simply logging into another Android phone running Lollipop. Also perfect for families who want to share a phone, but not their stuff</li>\r\n<li>Guest user for phones and tablets means you can lend your device and not your stuff</li>\r\n<li>Screen pinning: pin your screen so another user can access just that content without messing with your other stuff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">New Quick Settings</h3>\r\n<p>Get to the most frequently used settings with just two swipes down from the top of the screen</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New handy controls like flashlight, hotspot, screen rotation and cast screen controls</li>\r\n<li>Easier on/off toggles for Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and location</li>\r\n<li>Manually adjust your brightness for certain conditions. Then, adaptive brightness will kick in based on ambient lighting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Connectivity</h3>\r\n<p>A better internet connection everywhere and more powerful Bluetooth low energy capabilities</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Improved network handoffs resulting in limited interruption in connectivity. For example, continue your video chat or VoIP calls without interruption as you leave the house and switch from your home Wi-Fi back to cellular</li>\r\n<li>Improved network selection logic so that your device connects only if there is a verified internet connection on Wi-Fi</li>\r\n<li>Power-efficient scanning for nearby Bluetooth low energy (“BLE”) devices like wearables or beacons</li>\r\n<li>New BLE peripheral mode</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Runtime and Performance</h3>\r\n<p>A faster, smoother and more powerful computing experience</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ART, an entirely new Android runtime, improves application performance and responsiveness\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Up to 4x performance improvements</li>\r\n<li>Smoother UI for complex, visually rich applications</li>\r\n<li>Compacting backgrounded apps and services so you can do more at once</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Support for 64 bit devices, like the Nexus 9, brings desktop class CPUs to Android\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Support for 64-bit SoCs using ARM, x86, and MIPS-based cores</li>\r\n<li>Shipping 64-bit native apps like Chrome, Gmail, Calendar, Google Play Music, and more</li>\r\n<li>Pure Java language apps run as 64-bit apps automatically</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Media</h3>\r\n<p>Bolder graphics and improved audio, video, and camera capabilities</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lower latency audio input ensuring that music and communication applications that have strict delay requirements provide an amazing realtime experience</li>\r\n<li>Multi-channel audio stream mixing means professional audio applications can now mix up to eight channels including 5.1 and 7.1 channels</li>\r\n<li>USB Audio support means you can plug USB microphones, speakers, and a myriad of other USB audio devices like amplifiers and mixers into your Android device</li>\r\n<li>OpenGL ES 3.1 and Android extension pack brings Android to the forefront of mobile graphics putting it on par with desktop and console class performance</li>\r\n<li>A range of new professional photography features for Android Lollipop that let you\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Capture full resolution frames around 30 fps</li>\r\n<li>Support raw formats like YUV and Bayer RAW</li>\r\n<li>Control capture settings for the sensor, lens, and flash per individual frame</li>\r\n<li>Capture metadata like noise models and optical information</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>State of the art video technology with support for HEVC main profile to allow for UHD 4K 10-bit video playback, tunneled hardware video decoding to save power and improved HLS support for streaming</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">OK Google</h3>\r\n<p>Easy access to information and performing tasks</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Even if your screen is off, you can say "OK Google" on devices with digital signal processing support such as Nexus 6 and Nexus 9</li>\r\n<li>Talk to Google on the go to get quick answers, send a text, get directions and more</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Android TV</h3>\r\n<p>Support for living room devices</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>User interface adapted for the living room</li>\r\n<li>Less browsing, more watching with personalized recommendations for content like movies and TV shows</li>\r\n<li>Voice search for Google Play, YouTube and supported apps so you can just say what you want to see</li>\r\n<li>Console-style Android gaming on your TV with a gamepad</li>\r\n<li>Cast your favorite entertainment apps to your big screen with Google Cast support for Android TV devices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Accessibility</h3>\r\n<p>Enhanced low vision and color blind capabilities</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Boost text contrast or invert colors to improve legibility</li>\r\n<li>Adjust display to improve color differentiation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Now in 68+ languages</h3>\r\n<p>15 new additions</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basque, Bengali, Burmese, Chinese (Hong Kong), Galician, Icelandic, Kannada, Kyrgyz, Macedonian, Malayalam, Marathi, Nepali, Sinhala, Tamil, Telugu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">Device set up</h3>\r\n<p>Get up and running in no-time</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tap &amp; go: instant set up of your new Android phone or tablet by simply tapping it to your old one (requires NFC)</li>\r\n<li>Whenever you get a new Android phone or tablet, you can bring over your apps from Google Play automatically from any of your old Android devices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h3 class="text-title">And a whole lot more</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tap &amp; pay: easily manage multiple payment apps by quickly switching between them</li>\r\n<li>Print preview and page range support</li>\r\n<li>Revamped display for battery, Bluetooth, data usage, and Wi-Fi settings and new search functionality</li>\r\n<li>New device level feedback for Nexus devices in Settings &gt; about phone &gt; send feedback</li>\r\n<li>Easier sharing with\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Improved ranking of your options within the share menu</li>\r\n<li>Android Beam: lets you share a file with someone nearby by gently tapping the two devices together</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Where supported by the hardware, your device will wake up as soon as you pick it up or tap the screen twice</li>\r\n<li>Improved hardware keyboard accessory support including support for multilingual, emoji input, search key, and improved app and system key chords</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>With the new release of Android L the devices Motorola <a href="https://www.google.com/nexus/6/">Nexus 6</a> and HTC <a href="https://www.google.com/nexus/9/">Nexus 9</a> also available on Google Websites.These are the two devices that are running Android L out of the box and other flagship devices are still waiting for Kitkat/Android L update.Nexus 6 is Available for pre-order starting in late October.</p>\r\n<h2>Nexus 6 Specs:</h2>\r\n<div class="specs-content clearfix">\r\n<div class="col featured-specs one-third js-featured-specs">\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<p>5.96” 1440x2560 display (493 ppi)</p>\r\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\n<p>3220 mAh</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<h3>Camera</h3>\r\n<p>13MP rear-facing with optical image stabilization<br />\r\n2MP front-facing</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>Processor</h3>\r\n<p>CPU: Qualcomm Snapdragon<sup>TM</sup> 805 - Quad Core 2.7 GHz<br />\r\nGPU: Adreno 420<br />\r\nMemory: 32 GB, 64 GB</p></blockquote>\r\n<h2>Nexus 9 Specs:</h2>\r\n<div class="specs-content clearfix">\r\n<div class="col featured-specs one-third js-featured-specs">\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<p>8.9" IPS LCD</p>\r\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\n<p>6700 mAh</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<h3>Camera</h3>\r\n<p>8MP rear camera, 1.6MP front camera</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<div class="tablet-col border-box">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>Processor</h3>\r\n<p>CPU: 64-bit NVIDIA Tegra K1 processor 2.3 GHz<br />\r\nGPU: Kepler DX1<br />\r\nMemory: 16 GB &amp; 32 GB</p></blockquote>\r\n<address>We will come up with more detailed review and feature review of Android L and the Nexus 6 and 9 devices.Till then stay updated subscribe to us!!!</address>\r\n<address> </address>\r\n<address><em>Android</em> and other marks are <em>trademarks of Google</em> Inc and respective companies.</address>\r\n<address> </address>\r\n<address>Source : android.com</address>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Nexus 6 and 9 - Announced with Android 5.0 Lollipop Running out of the box', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1665'),
(1683, 1, 'Android Lollipop 5.0 has created some amazing user experience and software development and an overhaul change in the development of the history of Android as a mobile software.Everybody wants to experience the flavor of new Lollipop on their device which is very ambitious since all devices are not officially supported and cant run the 60fps animations smoothly.\r\n\r\nSo we have got the Android Lollipop launcher and the new Google Search 4.x version apks which run on any device smoothly from the nexus 6 system blob.\r\n\r\nNow you can install it on your Android phone to experience the bit of taste with any Android 4.1+ which means all the jellybean and above handsets.\r\n<blockquote><span style="color: #0000ff;">Complete walk-through of Android Lollipop coming soon on our You tube channel!!!</span></blockquote>\r\nAs we installed in our Micromax Unite 2 and our Nexus 7 2012(WiFi) model we got two new experience.\r\n\r\nMicromax Unite 2 running Android 4.4.2 Kitkat the app drawer animation which many of you identify Lollipop experience is not so amusing,The frame rate drops and the animations are not so smooth.On the other hand even after updating your Nexus 7 or 4 or 5, you will not the new app drawer and rather see the old one.So after updating our Nexus 7 we installed the launcher and it worked great as the OS has support for 60fps animation with some kernel optimizations which is slightly over-clocked for running the UI smoothly.\r\n\r\nHere are some screens of Android L Launcher and Google Search on Micromax Unite 2 and Nexus7.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/androidlscreenu2.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1695" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/androidlscreenu2.png" alt="androidlscreenu2" width="1000" height="2023" /></a>\r\n<h3>How to Install :</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>Download Android L Launcher from <a href="http://www.mediafire.com/download/52ww36zy3ci7kpg/com.google.android.launcher-1.1.1.1499465-101010-minAPI16.apk">here</a>.Install it as a normal apk.</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>If you have OK Google On then turn it off.To turn it off just go to Google Now-&gt;Settings-&gt;Voice-&gt;"OK Google" Detection and Turn It OFF.</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>And Now you can install the Google Search Updated APK from<a href="http://www.mediafire.com/download/xe7ucci23760k9c/com.google.android.googlequicksearchbox-4.0.26.1499465.arm-300400260-minAPI16.apk"> here</a>.</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3>Done enjoy Android L look n feel!!!</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Android L Launcher and Google Search app on Android 4.1+ devices', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1683'),
(1731, 1, 'MTS has launched a new WiFi enabled Data card which is a dongle with CDMA 2000 1x/3Gplus.It also supports IPv6 and you can connect up to 6 devices to its WiFi network which is like a hotspot or you can say a WiFi router.You get a travel charger with it with which you can access to internet through WiFi anytime just plug it to the charger and switch it on and it will be ready to give you the fastest internet experience.You get a user manual,a warranty card,dongle and the travel charger in the box contents.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_20141119_150440.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1733" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_20141119_150440-1024x764.jpg" alt="IMG_20141119_150440" width="720" height="537" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe specs on the back of the box says :\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_20141119_192219.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1737" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_20141119_192219-803x1024.jpg" alt="IMG_20141119_192219" width="720" height="918" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt costs a hefty 2650/-(MRP) but on the MTS site you can grab this for a promotional "GB Festival" price of Rs.999/-.It also supports a memory card reader inbuilt which supports up to 32 GB Memory Card.This dongle is compatible with all the Major OS distributions like Windows,Mac,Linux and Mint.\r\n\r\nYou can always run in other distros by manually setting up your Ethernet connection settings.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screenshot-2014-11-19-22.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1740" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screenshot-2014-11-19-22-1024x574.png" alt="Screenshot 2014-11-19 22" width="720" height="403" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe new WebUI Interface of MTS Mblaze makes it more interesting.Now Ubuntu,Mac Users no need to install any software as soon as you plug in the dongle it takes about 10 secs and starts a local server through which you can access the http://mblaze.mylink which gives you all the information about signal strength,no of WiFi devices connected and much more.\r\n\r\nWe ordered it on Monday morning and we got it on Monday evening and it got activated in just one day.If you want quick and effective customer support and high speed dongle its a must that you can buy this internet speed machine.If you have any queries on how to use or how to setup leave your queries down in the comments section below.\r\n\r\nIf you like to open a question for all then you can also post your questions on our dedicated Q&amp;A page where community is here to  help you.\r\n\r\nWant to ask a question click <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/dwqa-ask-question/">here</a>.', 'Unboxing the MTS Mblaze Ultra WiFi', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1731'),
(1815, 3, '<br />Well well,the CES2015 as big as ever has given us some mind boggling stuff to wait for...let me give you some examples:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The<em> Mercedes Benz F 015</em> luxury car with its jaw dropping interiors..the flashing lights..and ofcourse it''s self driven..straight out of a sci-fi movie..we don''t expect any less ;)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/benz.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1816" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/benz-300x196.jpg" alt="benz" width="300" height="196" /></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/b1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1824" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/b1-300x200.jpg" alt="b1" width="300" height="200" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The <em>Lenovo Vibe Xtension Selfie Flash</em>-it has seven LEDs in a circle and you can just plug it in the headphone jack for that drool worthy selfie.</li>\r\n	<li>The <em>Tonino Lamborghini 88 Tauri</em>...no guesses..it''s a $6000 priced android smartphone from the house of the finest car-makers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/l.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1817" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/l.jpg" alt="l" width="198" height="140" /></a></p>\r\nNow that I have set the tone let''s look out for technology that we can actually use in a year or two from now...\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="text-align: left;"><em>TrackR Bravo</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/track.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1818" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/track-300x194.jpg" alt="track" width="300" height="194" /></a></p>\r\nFor people amongst us who keep on forgetting things,here is some good news.The TrackR Bravo will help to find your missing objects using an intuitive android or IOS app.3.5 mm thin,starting at $29,available in variety of colors,use it as a keyring or stick it to your things,it sure keeps things interesting.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>SnapCam</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/snap.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1819" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/snap-300x200.jpg" alt="snap" width="300" height="200" /></a></p>\r\nJust 3.8cm square,you can control it with taps(1,2,3),clicks 8mp photos,records videos in 720p HD,you can also live stream using built in WiFi or bluetooth.3 colors and a price tag of around $150.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>The Ring</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/ring.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1820" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/ring-300x211.jpg" alt="ring" width="300" height="211" /></a></p>\r\nSci fi world again,ever imagined controlling everything with just a flick of your finger,be it clicking a pic,tweeting,or just controlling the lights,soon to be reality just you will need the Ring on your finger..the ring to control them all.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>The Dell XPS13</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DELL.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1821" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DELL-300x209.jpg" alt="DELL" width="300" height="209" /></a></p>\r\nDell claims it to be the smallest 13 inch laptop,it sports a 3200x1800 quad-HD display with a 5.2mm bezel bordering the screen.Starting at $799,Dell sure seems to be giving competition to Macbook Air.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Polaroid Zip</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/polaroid.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1822" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/polaroid-300x168.jpg" alt="polaroid" width="300" height="168" /></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/pol.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1823" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/pol.jpg" alt="pol" width="264" height="264" /></a></p>\r\nA photo printer that''s the size of a smartphone and about an inch thick..well that''s what the polaroid zip is.It can connect to your device using an app and bluetooth and you can print 2x3 photos or visiting cards...also there are whole lot of filters and stickers,stamps etc available...I sure would want this one..:)', 'The coolest gadgets to hit town this year - CES 2015', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1815'),
(1827, 1, 'In this tutorial I will show you guys how to decompile and recompile apk files on Ubuntu or any Linux distro.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 ways to do it.One way is to install it from the ppa repository which is stable but old version of apktool while other method is to get the latest stable version of APKTool from Google project site.I will show you the second method because it is easy to understand and faster to set up. Now the steps are as follows :\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Go to this URL : <a href="https://code.google.com/p/android-apktool/">https://code.google.com/p/android-apktool/</a> to see the documentation and other commands on how to use the tool.</li>\r\n	<li>To download the latest version move to this link : <a href="https://bitbucket.org/iBotPeaches/apktool/downloads">https://bitbucket.org/iBotPeaches/apktool/downloads </a></li>\r\n	<li>Download the apktool zip : <a href="http://www.mediafire.com/download/56fhlu6wnbtfdna/apktool.zip" target="_blank">Apktool.zip</a>.Extract the archive.</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot-from-2015-01-11-210317.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1873" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot-from-2015-01-11-210317-1024x576.png" alt="Screenshot from 2015-01-11 21:03:17" width="640" height="360" /></a></li>\r\n	<li>Open Terminal on Ubuntu.</li>\r\n	<li>Type the below command :</li>\r\n	<li>[shell]sudo nautilus[/shell]</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot-from-2015-01-11-210336.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1874" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot-from-2015-01-11-210336-1024x576.png" alt="Screenshot from 2015-01-11 21:03:36" width="640" height="360" /></a></li>\r\n	<li>Now Open the extracted folder which has apktool and apktool.jar copy both files.</li>\r\n	<li>Navigate to usr/local/bin and paste these files.</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot-from-2015-01-11-210446.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1875" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot-from-2015-01-11-210446-1024x576.png" alt="Screenshot from 2015-01-11 21:04:46" width="640" height="360" /></a></li>\r\n	<li>Right click on them and go to permissions tab and set them as executable.</li>\r\n	<li>Thats it you''re done.Now you can use apktool in terminal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNow to use apktool just open terminal and type apktool to get it going. See the video tutorial below for installation help and how to use apktool.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<center><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/1t5n8rR5hTE" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></center>&nbsp;', 'How to Install and Use ApkTool in Ubuntu 14.04', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1827');
