(1832, 4, '<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/micromax-yu-yureka-review1.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-1939" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/micromax-yu-yureka-review1-300x167.jpg" alt="micromax-yu-yureka-review" width="370" height="206" /></a><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Micromax-Yu-Yureka-reviews-b.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-1948" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Micromax-Yu-Yureka-reviews-b-300x198.jpg" alt="Micromax-Yu-Yureka-reviews-b" width="329" height="217" /></a>\r\n\r\nMicromax is India''s top domestic smartphone vendor and has plenty of popular products on offer. The company now wants products that will stand out and have strong individual identities - and that means making some bold moves. The result is Yu Televentures an all-new subsidiary company which will develop and sell smartphones aimed at the youth market. Yu will target budget-conscious buyers. These phones will only be available online.\r\n\r\n<strong>Specs:</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">Display :-5.5-inch 720p HD </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">OS:- Cyanogen OS 11, built on Android 4.4.4 OS </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">Processor:- 1.5GHz octa-core 64-bit Qualcomm Snapdragon 615 CPU </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5"> GPU:- Adreno 405 </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">RAM:- 2GB DDR3 </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">Storage Memory:- 16GB (12 GB available, can be expanded up to 32GB) </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">Camera:-13MP AF rear camera (Exmor Sony CMOS sensor, f2.2 aperture, 1080p @ 30fps, 720p @ 60fps) and 5MP front camera </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">Compatible Sim type:- GSM, GPRS, WCDMA and LTE </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">Battery:-2,500 mAh removable battery </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5">Price:-Rs 8,990 </span>\r\n\r\nThe big difference with the Yu Yureka is that it runs Cyanogen OS 11 and not stock Android. The phone offers its users much more customization than Android, maybe a bit too much for the price . Even Cyanogen has changed its OS a bit for Yu and you have a couple of themes exclusive to the brand. This is undoubtedly the biggest differentiator for the Yureka. The other interesting feature has to be the 13 MP camera, which is quite rare in a sub-Rs 10,000 phone. The camera is good, but by no means exceptional.\r\n\r\n<strong>Some Still Images taken from Micromax Yu Yureka:-</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_20150107_090458.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1943" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_20150107_090458-300x223.jpg" alt="img_20150107_090458" width="300" height="223" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_20150108_191806.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1944" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_20150108_191806-300x223.jpg" alt="img_20150108_191806" width="300" height="223" /></a><a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/cam-2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1945" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/cam-2-300x174.jpg" alt="cam-2" width="300" height="174" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/cam-10.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1946" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/cam-10-300x174.jpg" alt="cam-10" width="300" height="174" /></a> <a href="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/cam-11.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1947" src="http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/cam-11-300x174.jpg" alt="cam-11" width="300" height="174" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe phone works well and ticks all the boxes when you look at what you are paying for it in the end. While some of you might have been expecting more from the phone, the fact remains that it is a good value for money budget phone and not a mid-range phone that has found itself at a lower price band due to some divine intervention.\r\n\r\nCertainly, if you are in one of the cities where 4G is already available. Others can look at this as a different option in comparison to the Xiaomi Redmi Note and maybe even the Moto E, though this is slightly more expensive. You are definitely getting a bit more advantage for what you paid for this phone and the Cyanogen OS 11 gets you more boasting rights than other Android users.\r\n\r\nClick <a href="http://www.amazon.in/b?node=5606984031">here</a> to buy from Amazon.', 'Micromax Yu Yureaka : Should you buy it?', 'http://www.itechnospot.com/blog/?p=1832'),
